(SIGHS)

01:39.324 --> 01:42.160
(MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING)

01:51.461 --> 01:53.087
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

02:09.687 --> 02:10.729
(SNIFFS)

02:16.027 --> 02:18.404
(MELANCHOLY MUSIC CONTINUES)

02:30.208 --> 02:32.544
(RIDE PASSENGERS SCREAMING
IN DISTANCE)

02:32.627 --> 02:34.045
(BUS BRAKES SQUEAL)

02:34.838 --> 02:37.048
(DOOR HISSES OPEN)

02:37.131 --> 02:40.468
BUS DRIVER: All right, folks.
Last stop. End of the line.

02:40.552 --> 02:42.846
Grab your belongings
and head off the bus.

02:42.929 --> 02:43.930
Thank you.

02:54.816 --> 02:56.025
(BELL JINGLES)

03:03.032 --> 03:04.826
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

03:07.287 --> 03:09.706
BARKER: (ON LOUDSPEAKER)
<i>Welcome, ladies and gentlemen,</i>

03:09.789 --> 03:14.586
<i>to the greatest carnival
in the world.</i>

03:14.669 --> 03:18.089
<i>Spine-chilling attractions,
fun for all ages.</i>

03:18.172 --> 03:20.049
<i>Hurry! Hurry, hurry.</i>

03:22.385 --> 03:25.096
<i>Behold,
the beauties of the Orient,</i>

03:25.179 --> 03:29.309
<i>reenacting forbidden dances
for your education</i>

03:29.392 --> 03:31.019
- <i>and pleasure.</i>
- (CROWD APPLAUDS)

03:33.146 --> 03:35.857
<i>Games of chance,
games of skill.</i>

03:35.940 --> 03:39.110
MAN: Molly, look what
I got for you. Chocolates.

03:39.193 --> 03:41.571
You ready to go?
You got the sandwiches?

03:45.617 --> 03:49.662
BARKER: One last chance to
witness this supreme oddity.

03:49.746 --> 03:53.791
I must ask you, however,
to remember that this exhibit

03:53.875 --> 03:59.130
is being presented solely in the
interest of science and education.

03:59.213 --> 04:03.051
Where did it come from?
Is it a beast or is it a man?

04:03.134 --> 04:05.637
Come on in.
Come on in and find out.

04:05.720 --> 04:08.556
(CROWD CHATTERING)

04:08.640 --> 04:13.770
This creature has been examined
by the foremost scientists

04:13.853 --> 04:19.108
of both Europe and the
Americas, and pronounced a man.

04:19.192 --> 04:21.611
Unequivocally, a man.

04:23.154 --> 04:25.365
(MUMBLES INCOHERENTLY)

04:27.408 --> 04:30.203
He can go for weeks
with neither food nor drink

04:30.286 --> 04:32.455
and live entirely
on the atmosphere.

04:32.538 --> 04:36.626
But you're in luck because tonight
we're going to feed him one last time.

04:36.709 --> 04:37.710
Peach.

04:37.794 --> 04:40.088
(CHICKEN CLUCKING)

04:40.171 --> 04:43.257
There will be a slight additional
charge for this attraction,

04:43.341 --> 04:46.844
but it's not a dollar,
not 50 cent, but a quarter.

04:46.928 --> 04:50.056
One fourth of a dollar,
and you will see him feed.

04:51.099 --> 04:52.517
- (WINGS FLAP)
- Suckle on the blood

04:52.600 --> 04:55.144
- of reptiles and birds...
- (CHICKEN CLUCKING)

04:55.228 --> 04:59.607
Like a babe feeding on
its mother's milk.

05:00.525 --> 05:01.901
- (CHICKEN CLUCKS)
- (CROWD EXCLAIMS)

05:02.735 --> 05:04.529
(CLUCKING)

05:13.287 --> 05:14.288
(GRUNTS)

05:17.083 --> 05:18.501
- (GROWLS)
- (CHICKEN YELPS)

05:18.584 --> 05:19.877
- (CROWD EXCLAIMS)
- (GRUNTS)

05:20.628 --> 05:21.921
(CROWD GASPING)

05:22.005 --> 05:24.632
- (GEEK GROWLS)
- MAN: Bite it! Come on!

05:24.716 --> 05:27.218
(SHOUTS OF ENCOURAGEMENT)

05:27.301 --> 05:29.220
(CHICKEN CLUCKING)

05:29.303 --> 05:30.638
(GASPING HOARSELY)

05:30.722 --> 05:31.723
No.

05:32.557 --> 05:33.975
(MUMBLES INCOHERENTLY)

05:36.853 --> 05:38.646
(INHALES SHARPLY, PANTS)

05:38.730 --> 05:39.939
- (GRUNTS)
- (CHICKEN YELPS)

05:40.023 --> 05:42.108
- (WOMEN SCREAM)
- (LAUGHTER)

05:43.234 --> 05:44.736
(PEOPLE APPLAUDING)

05:47.071 --> 05:48.281
(GRUNTS)

05:49.407 --> 05:51.367
- (CROWD CHEERS)
- (WOMEN SHRIEK)

05:52.827 --> 05:55.747
WOMAN: Come on.
Fourth of a dollar.

05:58.791 --> 06:01.753
25 cents. Pay up.

06:01.836 --> 06:03.838
(CROWD SCREAMS, APPLAUDS)

06:04.922 --> 06:07.175
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

06:09.635 --> 06:12.388
BARKER: (ON LOUDSPEAKER)
<i>Step right up and get a prize!</i>

06:12.472 --> 06:13.848
MAN: Hey, mack.

06:13.931 --> 06:15.433
You can't be back here.

06:16.100 --> 06:17.477
You.

06:17.560 --> 06:19.812
You're the cluck
from the bus stop.

06:19.896 --> 06:21.689
You followed me here,
didn't ya?

06:22.482 --> 06:23.566
Why?

06:23.649 --> 06:24.776
What's your pitch, pal?

06:26.069 --> 06:28.613
You on the level?
You need work?

06:29.989 --> 06:30.990
He's jus
peddling applesauce.

06:31.074 --> 06:32.992
Major. Major.
Give me a minute.

06:35.119 --> 06:36.913
All right,
we got a storm coming through.

06:36.996 --> 06:39.540
I gotta load out fast.
I'm short a few guys.

06:39.624 --> 06:40.792
It's hard work.

06:40.875 --> 06:42.835
You get a dollar, you move on.
No mooching around.

06:42.919 --> 06:43.920
Savvy?

06:45.963 --> 06:47.965
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

06:50.301 --> 06:51.803
(WORKERS SHOUTING
INDISTINCTLY)

07:09.862 --> 07:13.449
All right, fellas,
on the count of three.

07:13.533 --> 07:14.826
Ready?

07:14.909 --> 07:18.329
- One, two, three.
- (WORKERS SHOUT INDISTINCTLY)

07:19.205 --> 07:20.248
Let her down.

07:20.331 --> 07:24.043
WORKER: Take the post down!
Take the post down!

07:27.421 --> 07:28.631
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

07:56.742 --> 07:58.619
Want I should help you
count it, Rockefeller?

08:00.288 --> 08:01.747
It was a dollar

08:01.831 --> 08:04.584
minus the till
for the Geek Show.

08:04.667 --> 08:07.336
That's right.
I clocked you, cluck.

08:12.466 --> 08:14.844
Hey! Hey!

08:14.927 --> 08:17.221
I'll give you five
for the radio.

08:19.182 --> 08:22.101
Tell you what,
we're joining another carnival

08:22.185 --> 08:24.604
about 20 miles
down the road.

08:24.687 --> 08:29.567
I'll give you the five,
plus a nice hot meal when we get there.

08:32.361 --> 08:34.739
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)

09:01.140 --> 09:02.767
(PLAYING GENTLE MELODY)

09:02.850 --> 09:04.227
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

09:25.373 --> 09:27.875
- (WHISTLE BLOWING)
- (CLAMORING)

09:27.959 --> 09:31.629
BARKER: Come on, fellas.
I need help. Chop chop.

09:32.797 --> 09:35.633
Hey, you.
Radio Flyer, come here.

09:40.304 --> 09:41.764
The Geek, he got loose.

09:41.847 --> 09:44.600
If you see him,
don't take him on your own.

09:44.684 --> 09:45.935
Let's get this fucker.

09:48.646 --> 09:50.523
Look under the truck.

09:50.606 --> 09:53.567
No, keep going.
To the funhouse.

09:55.653 --> 09:56.654
MAN: Hurry!

10:00.866 --> 10:02.159
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

10:02.243 --> 10:03.536
I'll let you in.

10:08.416 --> 10:09.875
(DOOR WHIRS)

10:11.794 --> 10:12.837
You go in there.

10:12.920 --> 10:15.131
If you see him,
push him through.

10:15.214 --> 10:16.716
I'll meet you
on the other side.

10:17.758 --> 10:19.760
(MACHINERY WHIRRING)

10:26.559 --> 10:28.394
- (MACHINERY WHOOSHES)
- (GASPS)

10:28.477 --> 10:29.562
(WHIRRING STOPS)

10:39.739 --> 10:41.407
(MUFFLED YELLING)

10:41.490 --> 10:43.075
(METAL CREAKS)

10:44.118 --> 10:45.619
(DOOR CLANGS AND HISSES)

10:50.958 --> 10:52.626
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

11:06.724 --> 11:08.392
(SOFT WHIMPERING)

11:11.687 --> 11:13.689
(PANTING WEAKLY)

11:19.236 --> 11:21.530
Hey, pal,
everybody's looking for ya.

11:21.614 --> 11:23.032
(GEEK MUTTERS)

11:25.242 --> 11:28.204
Well, I'm not gonna blow the whistle.
You didn't do nothing against me.

11:29.914 --> 11:31.248
Why don't you
come on out?

11:34.043 --> 11:35.586
Come on,
I'm not gonna hurt you.

11:35.669 --> 11:37.672
(GEEK MUTTERING)

11:42.760 --> 11:44.053
I am not like...

11:44.136 --> 11:45.638
I'm not like this.

11:45.721 --> 11:47.098
(BOTH GRUNT)

11:51.685 --> 11:52.686
Easy.

11:53.104 --> 11:54.355
Easy.

11:54.980 --> 11:55.981
(GRUNTS)

11:56.482 --> 11:57.858
(BOTH GRUNT)

11:59.318 --> 12:00.277
- (GEEK GROANS)
- Hey!

12:00.861 --> 12:02.488
Hey!

12:02.571 --> 12:05.616
Hey, you're gonna kill him.
Jesus, kid!

12:11.163 --> 12:13.082
Aw, jeez, is he dead?

12:13.165 --> 12:15.835
I don't need no shooflies in here, Clem.
Get him out of here.

12:16.544 --> 12:17.545
CLEM: In the back.

12:18.337 --> 12:19.964
The cage in the back.

12:20.047 --> 12:21.132
Hell.

12:21.215 --> 12:22.758
(CHICKENS CLUCKING)

12:24.552 --> 12:25.553
Jesus.

12:29.515 --> 12:30.516
(GRUNTS)

12:30.599 --> 12:32.601
Out, out! Go, go, go.

12:33.769 --> 12:35.521
- (GEEK GROWLS)
- Back!

12:35.604 --> 12:38.149
- Back, back, back!
- (GROANS)

12:38.232 --> 12:40.359
Step right up and behold,

12:40.443 --> 12:44.113
one of the unexplained
mysteries of the universe.

12:44.196 --> 12:46.615
Is he man or beast?

12:46.699 --> 12:48.742
(MUTTERS INDISTINCTLY)

12:48.826 --> 12:50.786
GEEK: (WEAKLY)
I'm not like this.

12:51.745 --> 12:54.039
(GEEK CRIES)

12:54.123 --> 12:58.461
CLEM: Folks will pay good money
just to make themselves feel better.

12:58.544 --> 13:01.505
- (CONTINUES CRYING)
- Look down on this fucker,

13:01.589 --> 13:03.841
grind some
chicken gristle.

13:05.342 --> 13:06.510
- How's your head?
- Hmm.

13:09.263 --> 13:10.347
Turn.

13:10.431 --> 13:11.682
Oh.

13:11.765 --> 13:12.766
(CLEM CHUCKLES)

13:15.311 --> 13:21.400
You can find a mattress
over there behind those jars.

13:21.484 --> 13:23.110
You can sleep
there tonight.

13:24.278 --> 13:25.654
Stay out of the rain.

13:25.738 --> 13:27.406
(CHICKENS CLUCKING)

13:31.452 --> 13:33.787
Go on, go on,
around the corner.

13:41.712 --> 13:45.132
Would a steady job be of
interest to you, young buck?

13:47.051 --> 13:49.428
Folks here,

13:49.512 --> 13:53.265
they don't make no never mind
who you are, or what you done.

13:53.349 --> 13:55.559
(LOW, UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING)

14:08.489 --> 14:09.990
(METALLIC TICKING)

14:10.074 --> 14:11.325
(IMPERCEPTIBLE)

14:13.118 --> 14:14.787
(SOFT METALLIC CLACKING)

14:22.878 --> 14:25.297
(GENTLE GUITAR MUSIC PLAYING)

14:28.884 --> 14:30.886
(RHYTHMIC TAPPING)

14:34.265 --> 14:35.266
Hey!

14:47.903 --> 14:49.363
- (VOCALIZES)
- (CHUCKLES) Yeah.

15:01.792 --> 15:03.002
- (SHOES CLATTER)
- (GUITAR MUSIC ENDS)

15:14.638 --> 15:17.308
(TRADITIONAL POP MUSIC
PLAYING ON RADIO)

15:31.572 --> 15:32.573
Mornin'.

15:33.824 --> 15:34.867
Mornin'.

15:36.660 --> 15:37.995
You got a tub?

15:38.078 --> 15:39.413
Certainly do.

15:41.206 --> 15:43.125
Just arrived last night,
so I thought...

15:45.628 --> 15:48.255
Of course you did.

15:48.339 --> 15:52.009
Well, it'll be a dime to use
it, and you get a cake of soap,

15:52.092 --> 15:54.553
and, uh, hot water.

15:58.599 --> 15:59.850
Leave the door open?

15:59.933 --> 16:02.811
Sure. But put that dime
on the table.

16:05.689 --> 16:09.568
Sorry to wake you, sugar.
I'm just getting a soak.

16:11.737 --> 16:13.906
MAN: I gotta go
into town anyway.

16:15.032 --> 16:16.742
Morning.

16:16.825 --> 16:19.411
And, uh, I'm going to see
about getting some breakfast.

16:19.495 --> 16:21.747
Now, sweetie, make sure
it's breakfast, okay?

16:21.830 --> 16:24.124
Promise Zeena you won't go
into some blind pig.

16:24.208 --> 16:26.126
Are you familiar
with those cards?

16:26.210 --> 16:27.711
Mm-hmm.

16:27.795 --> 16:29.380
And, uh, tarot.

16:29.463 --> 16:30.839
Very powerful stuff.

16:35.511 --> 16:38.389
Well, maybe Zeena
will read your fortune, uh,

16:38.472 --> 16:40.057
if you're lucky,

16:40.140 --> 16:41.809
after your bath.

16:47.147 --> 16:48.273
You could take
all your things off

16:48.357 --> 16:50.359
and hang 'em over the chair
there, nice and neat.

16:50.442 --> 16:53.612
MAN: I'll have <i>eggs a la
Benedict,</i> a croissant,

16:53.696 --> 16:58.409
<i>jus d'orange, cafe au lait,</i>
and, uh, ba-bum.

16:59.159 --> 17:01.203
<i>Au revoir, ma cherie.</i>

17:03.455 --> 17:04.455
(MATCH STRIKES)

17:07.334 --> 17:08.919
Gonna be helping
Clem out a bit.

17:10.212 --> 17:11.213
Clem, huh?

17:12.506 --> 17:14.133
- (MOANS)
- (ZEENA SIGHS)

17:14.215 --> 17:15.925
Say, maybe you can
hawk for me.

17:16.009 --> 17:17.594
You know,
work the audience.

17:17.678 --> 17:19.012
We got a little
mind reading show.

17:19.096 --> 17:20.388
What would I have to do?

17:20.472 --> 17:22.974
ZEENA: Ah, ain't nothin' to it.
Carny speak's like a song.

17:23.058 --> 17:27.521
We sound Southern to Southerners
and Western to Westerners.

17:28.564 --> 17:30.649
You got
a sweet little lilt.

17:30.733 --> 17:33.235
Just gotta lean on it.
Talk of the soil.

17:33.318 --> 17:36.155
You drawl slow, but all the
while, you're hustling fast.

17:39.908 --> 17:42.411
Yeah, you can
peddle for me.

17:42.494 --> 17:46.832
And on your down time,
maybe Pete can show you a trick or two.

17:46.915 --> 17:48.500
You're gonna do just fine,
honey.

17:48.584 --> 17:49.877
You got panache.

17:51.170 --> 17:52.171
(CHUCKLES)

17:54.006 --> 17:55.549
What is that?

17:56.258 --> 17:57.259
Well,

17:58.260 --> 18:00.179
you're easy on the eyes,
honey.

18:04.183 --> 18:05.559
(ZEENA CHUCKLES)

18:07.728 --> 18:08.979
Oh, you're trouble,
ain't you, pup?

18:09.062 --> 18:10.272
No, ma'am, I'm absolutely
no trouble at all.

18:10.355 --> 18:11.356
Oh, yes, you are.

18:11.440 --> 18:12.941
Yes, you are.
You're a "maybe."

18:14.985 --> 18:16.403
And "maybes"...

18:17.654 --> 18:19.406
(SIGHS)

18:19.490 --> 18:21.450
they're real bad for me.

18:25.954 --> 18:27.539
Well, ain't you one.

18:31.084 --> 18:32.836
- I better go.
- Yeah.

18:34.379 --> 18:37.216
Just try and get away,
you dope.

18:50.646 --> 18:53.482
(CARNIVAL MUSIC PLAYING)

18:53.565 --> 18:55.567
(GRUNTING)

18:57.319 --> 18:59.530
(CHEERING)

19:05.577 --> 19:09.039
Take over for me.
My knees are shot to shit.

19:09.122 --> 19:10.999
Always with the knees.

19:11.834 --> 19:13.502
I am The Major!

19:13.585 --> 19:15.504
The tiniest man
on record,

19:15.587 --> 19:20.092
master of the nami-jitsu,
the secret technique from the Orient.

19:20.175 --> 19:23.887
And $20 says I can beat
any of you yahoos

19:23.971 --> 19:25.681
in a wrestling match.

19:25.764 --> 19:26.849
Don't be bashful, folks.

19:26.932 --> 19:28.058
If there's any of you
that have a question for me,

19:28.141 --> 19:31.770
Mr. Carlisle will now be collecting
your cards and envelopes.

19:31.854 --> 19:33.605
Make sure to
write your questions

19:33.689 --> 19:36.149
and your name on a card
inside the envelope.

19:36.233 --> 19:37.317
All right, don't look
at anybody else's.

19:37.401 --> 19:38.819
WOMAN: Thank you.

19:38.902 --> 19:40.904
Let's just all just mind our manners,
and we'll stay out of trouble, now.

19:40.988 --> 19:42.614
There are five senses
we all possess.

19:42.698 --> 19:45.033
- Miss Molly, you have a question for us?
- No.

19:45.117 --> 19:47.160
All right. Well, you're not
gonna get an answer then.

19:47.244 --> 19:49.288
ZEENA: We all can hear, see,
touch, smell, and taste.

19:49.371 --> 19:52.541
ZEENA: However, I have been
blessed with a sixth one.

19:52.624 --> 19:56.545
A natural connection,
if you will, to the ether.

19:58.422 --> 20:01.258
Thank you for the envelopes,
Mr. Carlisle.

20:02.176 --> 20:03.677
(CROWD APPLAUDING)

20:05.095 --> 20:06.763
Choose your fate or the color
of your curtains...

20:06.847 --> 20:09.308
Zeena's cooking up
a good crowd out there, Pete.

20:09.391 --> 20:11.310
- You sauced? Come on, Pete.
- Oh...

20:11.393 --> 20:13.145
- Pete, Zeena's on.
- Oh?

20:13.228 --> 20:14.855
- (ZEENA TALKING INDISTINCTLY)
- I'll read the first card.

20:14.938 --> 20:16.023
(PETE MUMBLES)

20:16.773 --> 20:18.025
She gonna need it soon.

20:18.108 --> 20:19.651
Okay, Abigail.
Write it down.

20:19.735 --> 20:21.153
- Where's the chalk?
- Right here.

20:21.236 --> 20:23.864
People always ask me
if I have spirit aid.

20:23.947 --> 20:28.619
Well, folks, the only spirits I
control are the ones in this bottle.

20:28.702 --> 20:30.495
(CROWD LAUGHS)

20:30.579 --> 20:33.624
The spirits of alcohol.

20:33.707 --> 20:36.501
Worried about her mother.
Gonna be looking soon.

20:36.585 --> 20:38.045
And every card after that,
you understand?

20:38.128 --> 20:40.130
I know it, I know it.

20:42.174 --> 20:43.550
(CROWD EXCLAIMS)

20:43.634 --> 20:45.260
(APPLAUDING)

20:49.139 --> 20:52.517
The questions are now
in the ether.

20:52.601 --> 20:56.063
I've never touched them.
Never read them.

20:56.146 --> 20:58.732
I don't need to, 'cause I get
an impression right here.

20:58.815 --> 21:00.108
PETE: There you go, Zeenee.

21:02.444 --> 21:03.528
There's a woman

21:04.529 --> 21:05.948
worried about her mother.

21:07.157 --> 21:09.785
"Will mother get better?"

21:09.868 --> 21:11.119
(WHISPERS)
Pete's sauced.

21:12.788 --> 21:13.789
I'll go.

21:13.872 --> 21:15.332
ZEENA: Wait,
I'm getting a letter.

21:15.916 --> 21:17.668
Yes. It's an "A".

21:17.751 --> 21:18.835
That's me.

21:22.005 --> 21:24.216
Abigail?
Is that your name, dear?

21:24.299 --> 21:25.717
(CROWD GASPS IN AWE)

21:27.594 --> 21:29.846
I'd say your mother
had a lot of hard work...

21:29.930 --> 21:31.640
- (SLURRING) Molly.
- Which envelope is it, Pete?

21:31.723 --> 21:33.225
- It's... I don't know.
- This one?

21:34.101 --> 21:35.978
I can't remember.

21:36.645 --> 21:37.771
I'm sorry, Molly.

21:37.854 --> 21:39.398
ZEENA: Now, I will attempt
to read the next question.

21:39.481 --> 21:40.899
(MOUTHING)
I don't know which one it is.

21:40.983 --> 21:42.317
ABIGAIL: Madam Zeena.

21:42.401 --> 21:43.443
Tell me more.

21:44.361 --> 21:45.278
Please.

21:45.362 --> 21:47.781
WOMAN: Tell her, Madam Zeena.
If you can.

21:49.491 --> 21:54.913
You have a couple of brothers,
or sisters, haven't you?

21:54.997 --> 21:56.832
- No, I don't, ma'am.
- (CROWD MURMURING)

21:56.915 --> 21:58.250
Only one sister.

21:59.543 --> 22:01.336
My brother passed away.

22:04.715 --> 22:06.008
Ah, yes.

22:07.134 --> 22:08.385
But I see him.

22:09.052 --> 22:10.012
That's what threw me.

22:10.095 --> 22:13.557
Your brother is right here
this very minute.

22:14.725 --> 22:17.102
His hand is on your shoulder.

22:18.687 --> 22:21.023
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)

22:21.815 --> 22:22.983
Can you feel it?

22:25.485 --> 22:27.279
- Yes.
- (PEOPLE GASP)

22:27.362 --> 22:29.573
Yes, I felt
something.

22:29.656 --> 22:31.158
I felt his hand.

22:32.492 --> 22:34.327
Oh, God! Harry!

22:34.411 --> 22:37.039
(CROWD APPLAUDS, CHEERS)

22:46.340 --> 22:48.341
(SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES)

22:54.681 --> 22:56.683
- (MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)
- Are you okay?

22:56.767 --> 22:59.644
Oh, the poor woman,
she wanted to know more.

22:59.728 --> 23:01.938
- Of course she did.
- (SIGHS)

23:02.022 --> 23:03.857
- What did you tell her?
- Well, the truth.

23:03.940 --> 23:04.858
We missed a cue

23:04.941 --> 23:06.943
and I had to use a trick
to ease the crowd.

23:07.027 --> 23:08.320
It was just a trick.

23:09.237 --> 23:10.238
It hurt.

23:10.322 --> 23:12.741
PETE: Well, it's good.
It's good that you did that.

23:12.824 --> 23:16.328
Yeah, well,
I gave her an amulet.

23:16.411 --> 23:17.871
PETE: I'm sorry
I missed the cue.

23:17.954 --> 23:20.749
I don't know why you don't
keep it going for her.

23:20.832 --> 23:23.126
- Never do a spook show.
- Oh. (PUFFS)

23:23.210 --> 23:25.045
PETE: No good comes out
of a spook show.

23:25.128 --> 23:27.547
Is it so bad
to give her hope?

23:27.631 --> 23:29.758
It ain't hope
if it's a lie, Stan.

23:29.841 --> 23:30.884
(SIGHS)

23:32.302 --> 23:34.805
All right, well,
what are those cards then?

23:34.888 --> 23:36.181
Hmm? Tarot?

23:36.264 --> 23:37.724
Well, honey,
it ain't the same thing.

23:37.808 --> 23:41.144
No, I even run 'em over
for myself. And Pete.

23:41.228 --> 23:43.772
You always get
some kind of answer.

23:43.855 --> 23:46.066
I bought those for you
in Paris.

23:48.443 --> 23:49.986
We stayed at the Ritz.

23:50.070 --> 23:53.115
Ah. Held over four weeks.

23:53.198 --> 23:55.325
Ah... (SPEAKS FRENCH)

23:55.408 --> 23:57.494
(ZEENA CHUCKLES)

23:57.577 --> 24:00.997
I wrote most of
the word system on that tour.

24:01.081 --> 24:03.375
That's where
we perfected the act.

24:03.458 --> 24:04.543
Didn't we, George?

24:04.626 --> 24:06.044
Can you still do it?

24:13.385 --> 24:14.469
Eh...

24:16.054 --> 24:17.430
All right.

24:19.850 --> 24:21.852
Stanton...

24:21.935 --> 24:25.522
give Zeena an article.
Any article.

24:27.315 --> 24:28.316
(SWITCHES OFF RADIO)

24:29.484 --> 24:30.902
(WATCH TICKING)

24:34.239 --> 24:36.116
ZEENA: Please concentrate
on this object

24:36.199 --> 24:38.368
I have in my hand,
Professor.

24:43.331 --> 24:44.833
What can
you tell me?

24:45.834 --> 24:47.294
Wristwatch.

24:47.377 --> 24:48.378
Leather band.

24:49.171 --> 24:51.631
Brass, not gold.

24:53.008 --> 24:56.094
Oh. Old and worn down.

24:56.970 --> 24:58.513
Ah...

24:58.597 --> 25:00.432
But it's full of meaning...

25:01.600 --> 25:04.853
Ah, it wasn't
yours originally, was it?

25:04.936 --> 25:06.813
- (THUNDER RUMBLING)
- You took it, or...

25:08.899 --> 25:11.276
You stole it, didn't you?

25:11.359 --> 25:15.155
Oh, I see an older man.

25:15.238 --> 25:18.450
Oh, the boy hates him.

25:18.533 --> 25:23.371
Oh, the boy would love to be
loved, but he hates that man...

25:23.455 --> 25:24.497
(PETE GRUNTS)

25:25.790 --> 25:26.791
(SHUDDERS)

25:29.669 --> 25:30.837
Death.

25:32.047 --> 25:34.299
Death and the wish of death.

25:39.387 --> 25:40.764
He loved that watch.

25:40.847 --> 25:42.891
That was his pride,
my father.

25:44.643 --> 25:46.102
Was it now?

25:50.273 --> 25:51.358
No, no, no.

25:51.441 --> 25:53.068
That's it. That's it.

25:53.151 --> 25:54.152
(SNAPS FINGERS)

25:54.236 --> 25:55.445
That's it. (GRUNTS)

25:57.906 --> 25:59.032
(PETE SIGHS)

26:14.506 --> 26:15.632
It's, uh...

26:15.715 --> 26:17.050
It's all there.

26:21.680 --> 26:23.014
(MUMBLES)

26:28.311 --> 26:29.729
Now, you see,

26:30.772 --> 26:32.649
each word has a number,

26:32.732 --> 26:35.068
and that number leads you
to a different word.

26:35.819 --> 26:37.237
Ba-bum!

26:37.320 --> 26:39.531
Zeena feeds them to me.

26:39.614 --> 26:44.536
"Please concentrate on the object
I have in my hand, Professor."

26:44.619 --> 26:47.205
"Please",
"an object", 21.

26:47.289 --> 26:51.835
Emphasis on "concentrate" means
that it is old and worn down.

26:51.918 --> 26:53.086
Cheap.

26:53.169 --> 26:54.170
Ba-bum.

26:57.090 --> 26:57.966
But...

27:00.552 --> 27:02.554
you gotta know
how to read the mark.

27:03.596 --> 27:06.933
How they move
and talk, dress.

27:08.727 --> 27:11.813
People are desperate
to tell you who they are.

27:11.896 --> 27:13.940
Desperate to be seen.

27:14.024 --> 27:15.358
Ain't that the truth?

27:17.652 --> 27:19.779
Yeah, but how do you know
if you got 'em hooked?

27:20.780 --> 27:22.157
Well, you pause.

27:22.240 --> 27:23.366
ZEENA: That's right.

27:24.576 --> 27:26.036
You take a moment.

27:29.247 --> 27:32.959
"Would you excuse me, please?
I need a glass of water."

27:33.043 --> 27:34.836
Yeah, or you faint.

27:34.919 --> 27:37.213
Weakened by the effort.

27:37.297 --> 27:38.548
(PETE CHUCKLES)

27:39.966 --> 27:41.718
How'd you know
about my father, though?

27:42.552 --> 27:44.596
That's a stock reading.

27:44.679 --> 27:46.348
It's a "Black Rainbow."

27:46.431 --> 27:48.058
One size fits all.

27:48.641 --> 27:50.018
(SLURRING)

27:50.101 --> 27:53.688
Thrifty but generous,
private but friendly,

27:53.772 --> 27:55.440
and... and you,

27:56.274 --> 27:59.694
you hated him but loved him.

27:59.778 --> 28:02.197
Now, everybody's had
some trouble.

28:03.239 --> 28:05.283
Somebody they've hated.

28:07.077 --> 28:09.537
Shadow from their past.

28:14.376 --> 28:17.128
And usually for a boy,
it's the old man.

28:18.838 --> 28:20.465
Now, if the mark is older,

28:20.548 --> 28:24.761
you say you had, uh,
some present loss.

28:24.844 --> 28:26.179
But younger?

28:26.262 --> 28:27.389
It's the father.

28:28.056 --> 28:29.724
There's always a father.

28:36.815 --> 28:38.024
Well,

28:39.234 --> 28:41.444
I will take this to Clem.

28:43.113 --> 28:44.906
We had a good day today.

28:46.199 --> 28:47.200
A great day.

28:53.331 --> 28:55.667
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

28:57.627 --> 28:59.629
- (DOOR CLOSES)
- Oh, my sweet Pete.

29:01.464 --> 29:03.591
(CHUCKLES DRYLY)
He breaks my heart.

29:06.594 --> 29:09.722
No, no, no. No more belting
the grape for you, Pete.

29:09.806 --> 29:10.765
I promised Zeena.

29:10.849 --> 29:13.393
PETE: Oh, Zeena's
not gonna know, Clem.

29:13.476 --> 29:15.019
Just one bottle,
that's all.

29:15.103 --> 29:17.689
Okay. Last time.

29:18.440 --> 29:19.441
Just go.

29:19.524 --> 29:21.609
PETE: Bless you, Clem.
Bless you.

29:23.111 --> 29:25.363
(SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES)

29:29.534 --> 29:31.453
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

29:34.164 --> 29:36.166
(JARS RATTLING)

29:37.292 --> 29:40.003
These are my little angels.

29:40.086 --> 29:42.213
Set it down here.
That's his home.

29:43.089 --> 29:44.507
Uh, no.

29:44.591 --> 29:47.260
Face him the other way,
he's shy.

29:47.343 --> 29:50.763
Got to keep my beauties
pickled fresh.

29:50.847 --> 29:56.394
"Begotten by the same lust and threat
that got us all walkin' on this earth,

29:56.478 --> 29:59.856
"but gone wrong somehow
in the maternal womb.

29:59.939 --> 30:03.443
"Not fit for livin'."

30:03.526 --> 30:08.781
Most of 'em die right at childbirth,
or even inside the mother.

30:11.951 --> 30:14.829
Now, this one
is a rare one.

30:22.212 --> 30:23.588
- (SWITCH CLICKS)
- (MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

30:23.671 --> 30:25.089
Enoch.

30:26.466 --> 30:29.177
I named him
on account of the Bible.

30:29.260 --> 30:32.138
Little fucker killed his
mother right at childbirth.

30:32.222 --> 30:36.476
Flopped around for a couple of
days, brayin' like a calf.

30:36.559 --> 30:39.312
Eye follows you around
like 'em portraits.

30:42.106 --> 30:44.526
Red box, wood alcohol.

30:44.609 --> 30:46.402
Good for picklin',
bad for drinkin'.

30:46.486 --> 30:48.655
Poison, real poison.

30:49.989 --> 30:51.157
Blue box,

30:51.241 --> 30:53.451
sweet sugarcane,
double-cooked.

30:53.535 --> 30:57.956
Christ almighty, throat's sore
as a bull's ass in fly time.

30:58.039 --> 31:00.041
(MUSIC PLAYING FAINTLY
ON RADIO)

31:01.292 --> 31:02.627
Folks know
to come to me for it.

31:02.710 --> 31:04.546
Half a plug a quart.

31:04.629 --> 31:06.881
Never cop a quart.

31:06.965 --> 31:11.094
You gotta make the tin cling,
same as everybody else.

31:11.177 --> 31:12.554
I never touch the stuff.

31:13.888 --> 31:15.265
Ain't we virtuous?

31:15.348 --> 31:16.891
Just say you understand.

31:18.226 --> 31:20.144
- I understand.
- What do you understand?

31:23.273 --> 31:24.607
Never cop a quart.

31:24.691 --> 31:26.442
That's right.

31:26.526 --> 31:28.611
Toe the line,
don't fuck with me.

31:29.445 --> 31:30.697
That's the lesson.

31:35.451 --> 31:37.412
(MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

31:37.495 --> 31:38.580
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

31:38.663 --> 31:40.248
<i>Entrez.</i>

31:41.249 --> 31:42.875
Clem asked me
to deliver this to you.

31:42.959 --> 31:44.836
Six quarts of wood alcohol
for the show.

31:44.919 --> 31:46.379
Oh, yeah,
for the show.

31:46.462 --> 31:48.506
(CHUCKLES) That's a
pity, isn't it?

31:48.590 --> 31:50.008
You can just
put 'em there.

31:51.634 --> 31:52.760
(COINS CLINKING)

31:52.844 --> 31:54.053
Here you go.

31:55.722 --> 31:56.848
Hey, Pete.

31:56.931 --> 31:59.976
I'd love to learn anything
that you'd wanna teach me.

32:02.353 --> 32:03.563
Teach you?

32:05.148 --> 32:06.858
I understand
if you don't wanna

32:06.941 --> 32:09.527
give away your secrets.
(CHUCKLES)

32:09.611 --> 32:13.114
Uh, no. It's not that,
my boy. It's, uh...

32:13.197 --> 32:15.116
Well, it's just that
it's been some time

32:15.199 --> 32:18.536
since anybody's asked me
to teach them anything.

32:19.871 --> 32:21.581
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

32:21.664 --> 32:24.459
- You know where to find me.
- Yes, I do.

32:24.542 --> 32:25.835
Have a good day.

32:34.302 --> 32:36.804
(PEOPLE SCREAMING IN DISTANCE)

32:36.888 --> 32:40.475
Never court
the sins of lust or pride.

32:40.558 --> 32:46.856
I was turned into this sorrowful
shape, for I disobeyed my parents.

32:46.939 --> 32:49.108
They wanted
only my well-being...

32:49.192 --> 32:51.778
MOLLY: Born during
an electrical storm,

32:51.861 --> 32:55.990
the atmosphere charged
with electrostatic power.

32:56.074 --> 32:58.159
I am now able to
withstand thousands...

32:58.242 --> 32:59.952
- (ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)
- (CROWD EXCLAIMS)

33:00.036 --> 33:02.413
...upon thousands of volts

33:02.497 --> 33:05.249
as they will course
through my body.

33:06.959 --> 33:10.088
But you must be warned
to keep your distance,

33:10.171 --> 33:13.675
for this entertainment carries with
it the danger of electrocution,

33:13.758 --> 33:16.386
even for those
in close proximity.

33:17.970 --> 33:19.681
(CROWD SCREAMS)

33:23.893 --> 33:26.020
(CHEERING AND APPLAUDING)

33:28.648 --> 33:30.775
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)

33:31.776 --> 33:33.236
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

33:44.914 --> 33:46.416
(GEEK MOANS)

33:47.041 --> 33:48.501
(GEEK MUTTERS)

33:52.964 --> 33:54.966
GEEK: (SOFTLY)
I'm not like this.

33:55.049 --> 33:58.344
Not like this,
I am not like this.

34:07.812 --> 34:09.272
(GEEK BREATHES RAGGEDLY)

34:22.284 --> 34:24.286
(ORNAMENTS JINGLING)

34:29.125 --> 34:30.960
Molly.

34:31.043 --> 34:32.210
I wanna show you something.
You have a second?

34:32.295 --> 34:33.420
I just got a couple of
minutes before Zeena starts.

34:33.504 --> 34:34.630
MOLLY: Mm-hmm.

34:34.714 --> 34:37.091
So, uh, I saw your show,
and I think it's real good,

34:37.175 --> 34:39.302
but I got an idea
for your act.

34:39.385 --> 34:40.386
Now, in your show,
you just...

34:40.469 --> 34:42.346
You know,
you tell a little story.

34:42.429 --> 34:43.889
But what if
you showed them something?

34:43.973 --> 34:44.931
What do you
think of that?

34:45.016 --> 34:47.560
An electric chair,
and they put you in it.

34:47.643 --> 34:48.728
Manacles in,

34:48.811 --> 34:50.897
and the audience is going,
"What's going on here?"

34:50.980 --> 34:52.523
All of a sudden,
little guy comes shufflin' out

34:52.607 --> 34:54.192
with an executioner's hood.

34:54.275 --> 34:55.693
He pulls this lever,
and they get real scared.

34:55.777 --> 34:56.902
They think maybe
you're gonna die,

34:56.985 --> 34:58.446
and boom, you got them,
they're back on their heels.

34:58.529 --> 34:59.530
What do you say?

35:00.406 --> 35:02.200
You wanna execute me?

35:02.283 --> 35:03.534
Just for a second.

35:03.618 --> 35:04.786
Then you come back to life.

35:08.456 --> 35:09.624
You drew me?

35:11.167 --> 35:12.752
Yeah, I draw
what's on my mind.

35:12.835 --> 35:13.961
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

35:15.797 --> 35:17.298
You could make a living
at this.

35:17.381 --> 35:19.467
My mama used to put me in these
contests when I was a kid.

35:19.550 --> 35:22.804
I used to win all of them,
but I don't know, I just...

35:22.887 --> 35:25.640
Just something I've always done.
Helps me think.

35:25.723 --> 35:28.810
You do know this is
the Ragtag Opera, right?

35:28.893 --> 35:31.479
Nothing's really the best
of anything around here.

35:31.562 --> 35:32.855
Well, you're better
than this place.

35:32.939 --> 35:34.690
Maybe you think I'm
special, but I'm not.

35:34.774 --> 35:36.692
Well, maybe I see something
in you you don't see.

35:36.776 --> 35:38.736
- You do?
- I mean, it's possible.

35:40.154 --> 35:42.073
Maybe all this is
good enough for me.

35:42.156 --> 35:44.075
I don't believe you.

35:44.158 --> 35:47.203
If it's not good enough for me,
sure ain't good enough for you.

35:48.663 --> 35:49.622
What do you think?

35:50.164 --> 35:51.207
You look good.

35:51.874 --> 35:52.917
Think about it.

35:53.876 --> 35:55.878
(ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

36:00.716 --> 36:02.176
Okay, you got steps.

36:06.889 --> 36:07.974
Ready?

36:08.474 --> 36:09.684
Voila.

36:11.394 --> 36:13.020
Looks just like
the sketch, don't it?

36:15.731 --> 36:16.816
No, sit in the chair.

36:16.899 --> 36:19.861
You made this?
When did you make this?

36:20.987 --> 36:22.363
And put your hands
in there.

36:22.446 --> 36:23.447
- Like that?
- Yeah.

36:23.531 --> 36:25.032
- (METAL CLACKS)
- Oh!

36:25.116 --> 36:27.493
See that? Major.
That's drama.

36:29.328 --> 36:32.081
Now your job over here is
gonna pull this lever. Okay?

36:32.165 --> 36:33.249
Don't bend down
to talk to me.

36:33.332 --> 36:34.041
No, I'm not bending down.
I'm trying to show you.

36:34.125 --> 36:36.043
You're gonna
pull this lever back.

36:37.753 --> 36:40.006
No, you gotta do it with some
force, with some drama.

36:40.089 --> 36:42.300
Put your back into it,
two hands. You got it.

36:44.218 --> 36:45.761
(DRAMATICALLY) Ahh!
And the electricity is flying,

36:45.845 --> 36:46.971
everybody's horrified.

36:47.054 --> 36:48.472
Is she gonna live or die?
It's going back and forth.

36:48.556 --> 36:49.765
And then you're gonna
save the day,

36:49.849 --> 36:51.225
and you're gonna push it
forward, two hands.

36:51.309 --> 36:53.102
Really put some...
And that's it!

36:53.185 --> 36:55.313
Manacles come off,
smoke's coming out.

36:55.396 --> 36:56.314
I haven't rigged this yet,

36:56.397 --> 36:57.315
but these two areas
are gonna have sparks.

36:57.398 --> 36:59.400
I don't know about
all your gobbledygook,

36:59.483 --> 37:01.068
but I am not wearing this,
I tell you that.

37:01.152 --> 37:02.403
Oh, but it's so good.

37:02.486 --> 37:04.280
What are you all of a
sudden, an engineer?

37:04.363 --> 37:06.657
It's the same rubber mat as
before, same electrical current.

37:06.741 --> 37:08.451
Just a better show,
that's all.

37:08.534 --> 37:09.702
What does
this wheel thing do?

37:09.785 --> 37:10.953
That's bullshit.

37:11.787 --> 37:12.830
(STAN CHUCKLES)

37:12.914 --> 37:13.873
Tell you what.

37:15.082 --> 37:17.209
- I'll think about it.
- I'll do it.

37:17.293 --> 37:19.211
I think he's
onto something.

37:19.587 --> 37:20.588
Sure.

37:24.467 --> 37:25.718
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

37:26.594 --> 37:28.262
(ENGINE TURNS OVER)

37:28.346 --> 37:30.556
You going someplace special?

37:30.640 --> 37:33.059
Just driving Pete and Zeena
into town.

37:33.142 --> 37:34.560
You want us to pick up
something for you?

37:34.644 --> 37:36.062
Nah, I'm good.

37:40.399 --> 37:42.109
- What's it to you?
- BRUNO: Nothin'.

37:44.528 --> 37:48.240
You been bumpin' gums
with Molly a little too often.

37:48.324 --> 37:50.368
Just so happens
I knew her old man.

37:50.451 --> 37:52.286
I knew him really good.

37:53.079 --> 37:54.747
Old-time grifter.

37:54.830 --> 37:57.875
My guess, he wouldn't
have liked you at all.

37:57.959 --> 38:01.837
I promised him I'd take care of the
girl, and I'm gonna.

38:01.921 --> 38:04.966
I still got five good pounds
of meat and bone right here.

38:06.467 --> 38:08.844
Hurt that girl,
you get 'em all.

38:11.138 --> 38:12.306
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

38:13.808 --> 38:16.102
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

38:31.075 --> 38:33.160
STAN: What are you
still doing up out here?

38:34.704 --> 38:36.956
I had a dream.
I couldn't go back to sleep.

38:40.835 --> 38:42.044
Wanna tell me about it?

38:43.796 --> 38:45.131
It was about my dad.

38:48.009 --> 38:49.135
Did he pass?

38:51.595 --> 38:54.265
He was alive and smiling
in the dream.

38:54.348 --> 38:56.225
I'll bet you he was
handsome, wasn't he?

38:56.308 --> 38:58.394
Girls always
take after their daddies.

38:58.477 --> 38:59.854
MOLLY: Hmm.

38:59.937 --> 39:02.982
"Mary Margaret Cahill,
don't forget to smile," he said.

39:04.650 --> 39:07.445
I don't really like to smile,
but I'd sure as hell smile for him.

39:08.738 --> 39:10.740
He could charm his way
out of anything.

39:10.823 --> 39:12.658
A man after my own heart.

39:13.784 --> 39:15.578
- Tell me more.
- About him?

39:16.495 --> 39:17.830
Sure, about you.

39:19.790 --> 39:21.083
What about me?

39:30.134 --> 39:32.136
I know that, uh,
you like chocolates,

39:33.054 --> 39:35.056
and you like to read.

39:35.139 --> 39:37.183
- And dancing.
- (CHUCKLES)

39:37.266 --> 39:38.809
When was the last time
you did?

39:38.893 --> 39:40.519
- A while.
- Yeah?

39:44.899 --> 39:46.192
We gonna fix that.

39:50.029 --> 39:51.280
You ready?

39:51.363 --> 39:52.823
- (CAROUSEL POWERS UP)
- Giddy up.

39:52.907 --> 39:55.201
(CAROUSEL MUSIC PLAYING
ON SPEAKER)

40:02.124 --> 40:04.293
- (STAN HUMS ALONG TO MUSIC)
- (MOLLY CHUCKLES)

40:11.675 --> 40:13.594
I've been thinking
about what you said, Stan.

40:13.677 --> 40:15.179
- What did I say?
- (MOLLY GRUNTS)

40:15.262 --> 40:16.597
(BOTH LAUGH)

40:16.680 --> 40:17.848
I remember.

40:19.308 --> 40:20.643
And where would we go?

40:25.731 --> 40:28.984
What if I told you I can get my
hands on a two person act for us?

40:30.528 --> 40:32.488
What are you
talking about?

40:32.571 --> 40:35.741
I'm talking about an act
that would get us headlining

40:35.825 --> 40:37.701
in the biggest hotels
and showrooms

40:37.785 --> 40:39.578
from the East Coast
to the West Coast.

40:39.662 --> 40:40.621
You're dreaming.

40:40.704 --> 40:43.749
No, Molly.
You're bigger than this place.

40:43.833 --> 40:46.627
If you let me, I wanna give you
the world and everything in it.

40:56.470 --> 40:57.471
Molly.

40:57.555 --> 40:59.557
(CAROUSEL MUSIC CONTINUES)

41:09.358 --> 41:10.734
(CURTAIN CLINKING)

41:16.407 --> 41:18.617
(ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

41:29.420 --> 41:30.880
(STAN PANTING)

41:34.091 --> 41:35.926
Come on.
I need a hand.

41:37.094 --> 41:39.013
Wound on his head
went bad.

41:39.096 --> 41:40.598
Flies got to it.

41:41.724 --> 41:44.059
Fever won't come down.

41:44.143 --> 41:47.396
- Is he dead?
- No. But he's bound to be.

41:56.071 --> 41:57.156
You heard?

41:57.239 --> 41:59.408
That little Kraut, the one
that looks like Chaplin,

41:59.491 --> 42:00.826
he just invaded Poland!

42:00.910 --> 42:02.786
The balls on him.
Put him here.

42:06.540 --> 42:07.917
(DOORBELL RINGING)

42:09.251 --> 42:11.712
- Come on!
- You gonna wait?

42:11.795 --> 42:13.214
And answer questions? No!

42:13.297 --> 42:15.257
They'll take him,
they'll care for him.

42:15.341 --> 42:17.718
- Put him under the...
- I said leave him be!

42:17.801 --> 42:19.261
Can't leave him in the rain.

42:19.345 --> 42:22.139
Don't pretend
you give a shit with me.

42:22.223 --> 42:24.183
You hungry?
I'm starving!

42:24.266 --> 42:26.685
Come on! Steak and eggs, on me.

42:33.776 --> 42:36.237
Sweetie, uh,
salt and pepper, please.

42:39.281 --> 42:41.200
How do you ever
get a guy to geek?

42:44.245 --> 42:47.289
Oh, I ain't gonna crap you up.
It ain't easy.

42:47.373 --> 42:49.667
You gotta pick up
a broken drunk.

42:49.750 --> 42:52.461
A real alkie,
a two bottle-a-day fool, see?

42:52.544 --> 42:53.754
Pick him up from where?

42:53.837 --> 42:56.882
Nightmare alleys, train tracks,
flophouses, you name it.

42:58.676 --> 43:04.223
Lot of folks came back from the war
addicted to the poppy, to booze.

43:04.306 --> 43:09.353
Now, opium really sinks its claws,
but you reel 'em in with booze.

43:11.105 --> 43:12.982
You tell 'em,

43:13.065 --> 43:16.068
"I got a little job for you.
It's a temporary job."

43:16.151 --> 43:17.987
Make sure you
emphasize that.

43:18.070 --> 43:21.907
"Just temporary, until we
get ourselves another geek."

43:28.289 --> 43:31.250
You spike it with
that opium tincture.

43:31.333 --> 43:33.544
One drop per bottle,
that's all.

43:34.420 --> 43:35.337
But, oh...

43:35.421 --> 43:39.049
oh, now, this is what
he thinks is heaven.

43:39.133 --> 43:42.177
So, you say to him like this,
you say to him,

43:42.261 --> 43:45.389
"Well, I gotta get me
a real geek."

43:45.472 --> 43:47.808
He says,
"Ain't I doing okay?"

43:47.891 --> 43:50.102
You say, "Like crap
you're doing okay.

43:50.185 --> 43:52.688
"You can't draw a real
crowd faking a geek.

43:52.771 --> 43:53.772
"You're through."

43:53.856 --> 43:55.065
And you walk off.

44:00.779 --> 44:02.698
Now, that night,

44:02.781 --> 44:06.994
you drag out the lecture,
you lay it on thick.

44:07.077 --> 44:11.165
All the while you're talking,
he's thinking about sobering up,

44:11.248 --> 44:15.002
getting the crawling shakes,
the screaming, the terrors.

44:16.879 --> 44:20.049
You give him time to think
that over while you're talking.

44:22.092 --> 44:25.095
Then, you throw him
the chicken.

44:25.679 --> 44:27.097
He'll geek.

44:27.431 --> 44:28.432
Jesus.

44:30.476 --> 44:31.560
Poor soul.

44:37.191 --> 44:38.192
Like this.

44:39.068 --> 44:41.028
Index, middle finger,

44:41.111 --> 44:44.239
half bent,
parallel to your thumb.

44:44.323 --> 44:47.868
As if you're going to pluck
something out of the air.

44:47.951 --> 44:49.620
Left hand on your temple.

44:49.703 --> 44:53.749
This means you're asking
for color, texture, specifics.

44:55.793 --> 44:56.919
That's it.

44:57.002 --> 44:58.962
STAN: You got
quite a gift.

44:59.046 --> 45:01.131
I don't know
how you do it, Pete.

45:01.215 --> 45:02.466
Keep all that
in your head,

45:02.549 --> 45:05.135
at the same time
entertaining all these folks.

45:08.097 --> 45:09.390
(PETE CHUCKLES)

45:11.141 --> 45:12.476
You know, if, um...

45:18.065 --> 45:20.150
If you're good
at reading people,

45:20.234 --> 45:23.445
it's mostly because
you learned as a child,

45:23.529 --> 45:27.324
trying to stay one step ahead
of whatever tormented you.

45:29.785 --> 45:33.831
Now, if they really did
a number on you,

45:33.914 --> 45:36.583
then that crack,
it's a hollow.

45:37.543 --> 45:39.753
And there'll
never be enough.

45:39.837 --> 45:41.964
There's no
filling that in.

45:42.047 --> 45:44.091
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING
IN DISTANCE)

45:45.467 --> 45:46.593
(PETE GRUNTS)

45:47.469 --> 45:49.263
Uh...

45:49.346 --> 45:52.474
Clem is breaking in
a new geek.

45:52.558 --> 45:54.226
Holding out on him.

45:55.352 --> 45:56.270
Poor bastard.

45:56.353 --> 45:59.148
He's gotta be
half out of his mind by now.

46:03.902 --> 46:07.197
I think George and I
will sleep below tonight.

46:10.367 --> 46:12.494
Stan, my boy.

46:12.578 --> 46:14.955
Would you be
so kind as to...

46:15.038 --> 46:18.459
as to procure me
a pint of the sugarcane?

46:18.542 --> 46:22.463
Pete, close your eyes
and go to bed.

46:22.546 --> 46:24.506
I need an incentive, son.

46:26.925 --> 46:27.926
Hmm.

46:31.597 --> 46:32.931
I'll see what I can do.

46:33.015 --> 46:34.224
Attaboy.

46:36.310 --> 46:38.645
(OPERATIC MUSIC PLAYING
ON RADIO)

46:38.729 --> 46:40.522
(JAR RATTLING SOFTLY)

46:45.027 --> 46:47.488
(METAL BANGING)

46:47.571 --> 46:49.406
- (CHICKEN CLUCKING)
- (GEEK GRUNTS)

46:52.034 --> 46:53.327
(GRUNTS)

46:53.410 --> 46:55.829
(OPERATIC MUSIC CONTINUES)

47:00.501 --> 47:02.461
(WOMAN LAUGHING)

47:02.544 --> 47:03.837
WOMAN: Jesus.

47:04.505 --> 47:06.381
You got no rhythm.

47:06.465 --> 47:08.634
(OPERATIC MUSIC CONTINUES)

47:14.723 --> 47:15.807
(COIN CLATTERS)

47:24.149 --> 47:25.484
(PANTING)

47:30.906 --> 47:32.157
(SNORING SOFTLY)

47:38.997 --> 47:41.333
(SOFT SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC
PLAYING)

47:52.177 --> 47:53.929
- What are you doing?
- Uh...

47:54.012 --> 47:56.473
I didn't mean any harm by it,
Pete. I was just curious.

47:58.433 --> 48:01.895
Stan, this book,
it can be misused.

48:01.979 --> 48:03.897
Do you understand?

48:03.981 --> 48:07.109
It's why I stopped
doing the act.

48:08.151 --> 48:10.779
I got shuteye.

48:10.862 --> 48:16.535
When a man believes his own lies,
starts believing that he has the power,

48:17.494 --> 48:19.871
he's got shuteye.

48:19.955 --> 48:22.165
Because now he believes
it's all true.

48:23.917 --> 48:28.213
And people get hurt.
Good, God-fearing people.

48:28.964 --> 48:32.884
And then you lie.
You lie.

48:32.968 --> 48:37.055
And when the lies end,
there it is.

48:37.139 --> 48:40.267
The face of God,
staring at you straight.

48:40.350 --> 48:42.102
No matter where you turn.

48:44.229 --> 48:47.190
No man can
outrun God, Stan.

48:50.694 --> 48:51.737
Yes, sir.

49:04.875 --> 49:06.251
(TRAPDOOR CLOSES)

49:06.335 --> 49:08.420
(FOOTSTEPS OVERHEAD)

49:08.503 --> 49:09.921
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

49:11.298 --> 49:12.341
(SIGHS)

49:13.550 --> 49:14.468
(SMACKS LIPS)

49:14.551 --> 49:17.054
(WHISPERING)
Middle and index finger bent,

49:17.137 --> 49:19.681
parallel to the thumb.

49:19.765 --> 49:22.768
Raise your left hand to your temple,
middle and index finger bent.

49:22.851 --> 49:24.811
Parallel to your thumb.

49:24.895 --> 49:26.730
Raise your hand
to your temple.

49:28.273 --> 49:30.150
Asking for
something specific.

49:31.360 --> 49:32.944
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

49:53.632 --> 49:57.636
ZEENA: No! No! Where is he?
Where is he?

49:57.719 --> 49:59.137
Pete! Come on!

49:59.221 --> 50:00.305
BRUNO: Zeena!

50:00.389 --> 50:02.015
Hey, Clem, we got a problem!

50:05.477 --> 50:07.771
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

50:08.939 --> 50:10.482
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

50:16.655 --> 50:19.616
It's Pete. He finally
did it to himself.

50:20.158 --> 50:21.535
He ain't moving.

50:25.622 --> 50:28.375
ZEENA: (SOBBING)
Pete. Oh, my... Pete.

50:29.835 --> 50:31.586
(CONTINUES SOBBING)

50:37.634 --> 50:39.010
Pete!

50:42.389 --> 50:45.559
(CONTINUES SOBBING)
Pete! Pete!

50:53.150 --> 50:55.444
BARKER: Sin and salvation.
Heaven and Hell.

50:55.527 --> 50:58.530
Find out what it feels like
right here on Earth.

50:58.613 --> 51:03.410
Let the mirrors show you who
you are and who you shall be.

51:03.493 --> 51:05.328
Hurry, hurry, hurry!

51:12.169 --> 51:14.171
CLEM: (ON LOUDSPEAKER)
<i>Spine-chilling rides!</i>

51:14.254 --> 51:16.089
<i>Fun for all ages!</i>

51:18.049 --> 51:21.344
<i>The sensation of the century!</i>

51:23.722 --> 51:27.601
<i>Ten attractions
for a single ticket.</i>

51:27.684 --> 51:29.853
(SIRENS APPROACHING)

51:36.526 --> 51:38.528
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

51:39.988 --> 51:41.740
<i>Hurry, hurry, hurry.</i>

51:41.823 --> 51:44.075
<i>Step right up and get a prize.</i>

51:47.954 --> 51:48.914
- Clem!
- CLEM: Yeah.

51:48.997 --> 51:50.081
- Clem!
- Yeah.

51:50.165 --> 51:52.542
Shooflies. I saw four cop cars
coming up the South.

51:52.626 --> 51:53.835
Oh, shit.

51:53.919 --> 51:56.046
They see the geek,
we're all wet.

51:56.922 --> 51:58.173
I'll stash him.

51:58.256 --> 52:00.550
You drop the banner,
chisel them a bit,

52:00.634 --> 52:02.135
buy me some time.

52:02.219 --> 52:03.512
Round up all the carnies

52:03.595 --> 52:05.931
and take them over
to that stage over there.

52:06.014 --> 52:07.724
CLEM: Whoopsie daisy. (GRUNTS)

52:10.018 --> 52:12.771
Move it, move them! Move them!

52:12.854 --> 52:14.481
STAN: Officer, what seems
to be happening?

52:14.564 --> 52:15.732
Join the others.

52:15.816 --> 52:17.692
Is that a warrant?
What's that for?

52:17.776 --> 52:19.694
Don't try to
pull that legal stuff.

52:19.778 --> 52:22.280
We're gonna close this whole
joint down one way or another.

52:22.364 --> 52:23.281
STAN: Yes, sir.

52:23.365 --> 52:25.575
OFFICER: ...that you
are carrying around...

52:25.659 --> 52:27.577
- (MUTTERS INDISTINCTLY)
- ...an illegal performance

52:27.661 --> 52:31.122
emphasizing cruelty
to both animal and man.

52:31.206 --> 52:33.291
And you, young lady.

52:33.375 --> 52:36.336
We have got wives
and daughters in this town.

52:36.419 --> 52:39.923
You are under arrest for indecency.
Get her down!

52:40.006 --> 52:43.593
No, stop! Stop!
Get down off there!

52:43.677 --> 52:45.095
- OFFICER: I'll club you down.
- The wheel is turning.

52:45.178 --> 52:46.805
The electrical current's
gotta go somewhere.

52:46.888 --> 52:48.598
Major, please!

52:48.682 --> 52:50.976
If you just permit us, sir,
you can judge in a fair manner

52:51.059 --> 52:52.269
- like the good King Solomon.
- (CROWD EXCLAIMS)

52:52.352 --> 52:53.478
Everybody, back off!

52:53.562 --> 52:55.230
(ELECTRICITY SURGING)

52:57.357 --> 52:59.943
- (ELECTRICITY POPPING)
- (CROWD SCREAMING)

53:00.026 --> 53:02.445
- (GRUNTS)
- (CRACKLING STOPS)

53:02.529 --> 53:04.865
That's why she's forced to wear
the brief as a covering, sir.

53:04.948 --> 53:06.199
She purges the current.

53:06.533 --> 53:07.534
Molly?

53:08.326 --> 53:09.619
Molly? You okay?

53:09.703 --> 53:11.454
(CROWD MURMURING)

53:14.124 --> 53:15.500
BRUNO: Make way.

53:15.584 --> 53:17.294
She just saved
your deputies' lives.

53:17.377 --> 53:18.628
Molly, Molly.

53:18.712 --> 53:21.172
I am closing you down.

53:21.256 --> 53:23.258
I ain't none of
your thieving southern police

53:23.341 --> 53:27.888
kissing a priest's toe on Sundays
and raking in graft six days a week.

53:28.638 --> 53:30.181
STAN: Is your name Jeremiah?

53:30.265 --> 53:33.018
Jeremiah, Jeremiah...
J... Jer... J... J...

53:33.768 --> 53:35.270
Jedediah Judd.

53:37.063 --> 53:38.273
Yeah.

53:40.984 --> 53:42.068
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

53:42.152 --> 53:44.070
A matter of the utmost
importance has arisen, sir.

53:44.154 --> 53:46.615
If I could just have
a minute of your time.

53:46.698 --> 53:48.283
A message has come through.

53:48.366 --> 53:51.953
And I think you're gonna wanna hear it,
but not in front of these kind folks.

53:52.037 --> 53:53.121
Please, sir.

53:56.458 --> 53:57.459
(SIGHS)

53:58.293 --> 53:59.294
Nobody leaves.

53:59.377 --> 54:02.380
Thank you.
Thank you.

54:02.464 --> 54:05.550
My name is Stanton Carlisle,
Marshal Judd, and my family's Scot.

54:05.634 --> 54:08.428
Scots are gifted with what the old
folks used to call "second sight."

54:08.511 --> 54:09.888
Now, it's clear to me,
for example,

54:09.971 --> 54:11.806
that you are a man
who is generally distrustful,

54:11.890 --> 54:13.767
but also fiercely loyal.

54:13.850 --> 54:15.518
I'd say that's a
fair description.

54:15.602 --> 54:16.937
And, uh, this is
none of my business

54:17.020 --> 54:19.564
because I know that you are capable
of handling your own affairs

54:19.648 --> 54:24.152
and anything else liable to come
along, but I do sense a childhood

54:24.736 --> 54:25.946
marred in disease.

54:26.029 --> 54:27.822
And it makes you, uh,

54:27.906 --> 54:30.951
feel hemmed in by it,
trapped, even to this day.

54:32.410 --> 54:33.828
And I sense a curio
of some kind.

54:33.912 --> 54:35.038
An amulet, a memento.

54:35.121 --> 54:37.165
You carry it on your person,
you had it for a long time.

54:37.248 --> 54:38.375
Who's Mary?

54:40.460 --> 54:41.461
A saintly woman.

54:42.837 --> 54:43.964
(GASPS SOFTLY)

54:44.839 --> 54:45.966
My... My mother.

54:46.049 --> 54:47.342
May I see it?

54:48.259 --> 54:50.178
May I see it, sir?

54:56.518 --> 54:57.560
Yes.

54:59.354 --> 55:00.522
She wants you to know

55:00.605 --> 55:02.857
that your ailment has not
shunned you from greatness,

55:02.941 --> 55:04.192
quite the contrary.

55:04.275 --> 55:07.654
Your community loves you and
feels protected by you, sir.

55:07.737 --> 55:09.614
And yes, you couldn't serve
your country on foreign soil,

55:09.698 --> 55:11.574
but you protect us
here at home.

55:12.993 --> 55:14.995
And this medal,

55:15.078 --> 55:17.956
this medal should be a
reminder of her love for you.

55:18.039 --> 55:19.332
And as long as
you just keep it here,

55:19.416 --> 55:22.043
close to your heart,
where our Lord Jesus Christ resides,

55:22.127 --> 55:24.963
it's gonna protect you
in the future.

55:25.046 --> 55:28.258
And she wants you
to know this, sir.

55:28.341 --> 55:32.846
It's only by being merciful to
others that a man has true power.

55:35.306 --> 55:37.225
(JUDD BREATHES DEEPLY)

55:39.227 --> 55:40.979
(CROWD APPLAUDING
AND CHEERING)

55:41.062 --> 55:42.647
But once I copped the
warrant off that deputy,

55:42.731 --> 55:44.065
I saw the marshal's name.

55:44.149 --> 55:45.984
I knew it was
a lead-pipe cinch.

55:46.067 --> 55:48.653
(ALL LAUGHING)

55:48.737 --> 55:50.655
You know what's funny?
Pete used to always say,

55:50.739 --> 55:51.781
"It's not the clothes,
but the shoes

55:51.865 --> 55:53.199
"that could tell you
everything you need to know

55:53.283 --> 55:54.576
- "about a man."
- Right.

55:54.659 --> 55:57.412
And he had a lift
in his right shoe.

55:57.495 --> 55:59.873
And I bet you he had polio
or something as a kid.

55:59.956 --> 56:01.708
You know, the military never
letting him in, mama's boy.

56:01.791 --> 56:02.917
I could tell by
the look in his eyes.

56:03.001 --> 56:04.002
That's good.

56:04.085 --> 56:05.045
Well, it takes one
to know one.

56:05.128 --> 56:07.255
- (CHUCKLES)
- He tried to railroad us, Clem,

56:07.338 --> 56:09.090
with that
fancy moustache.

56:09.174 --> 56:11.051
I saw that chain
around his neck,

56:11.134 --> 56:12.969
I got it out of him,
Saint Christopher medal,

56:13.053 --> 56:14.971
all that Bible talk.

56:15.055 --> 56:17.098
I thought, well,
he must know somebody named Mary.

56:17.182 --> 56:18.975
Right.

56:19.059 --> 56:21.603
And lo and behold,
the Lord blessed us.

56:21.686 --> 56:23.188
His mother's
name's Mary.

56:23.271 --> 56:24.647
- You had him!
- (CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

56:29.527 --> 56:31.488
(PANTING) Molly,
I was looking for you.

56:31.571 --> 56:33.156
You all right?

56:35.950 --> 56:37.202
I'm ready, Stan.

56:37.994 --> 56:39.370
Ready for what?

56:39.454 --> 56:41.915
To leave all this behind,
go with you.

56:44.834 --> 56:46.586
- We are ready, aren't we?
- (LAUGHS)

56:46.669 --> 56:48.213
- You saw me out there.
- I sure did.

56:48.296 --> 56:49.547
My whole life I've been
looking for something,

56:49.631 --> 56:51.007
something that I'm good at.
And I think I found it, Molly.

56:51.091 --> 56:52.092
I think I'm ready.

56:52.175 --> 56:54.469
I know you are, Stan.
(CHUCKLES)

56:54.552 --> 56:57.347
- (SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)
- STAN: Hmm.

56:57.430 --> 56:59.724
And I know you'll always
look after me, right?

57:00.683 --> 57:02.393
I will if you let me.

57:04.020 --> 57:05.355
What about Zeena?

57:06.773 --> 57:08.358
Because of Pete?

57:08.441 --> 57:10.944
- Well, I don't wanna hurt her.
- Oh, you won't.

57:11.027 --> 57:15.073
Zeena's lived. She's, uh...
She knows what's what.

57:15.156 --> 57:17.826
Everybody knows you're the one
I've been pining after.

57:17.909 --> 57:20.328
Molly, you're the reason
I've stuck around.

57:30.255 --> 57:31.840
(LIVELY CHATTER)

57:33.883 --> 57:35.009
You seen Molly?

57:35.093 --> 57:37.387
(LIVELY JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)

57:37.470 --> 57:38.471
Hmm?

57:40.181 --> 57:41.182
Stan?

57:41.975 --> 57:43.518
- (KISSING)
- Stan?

57:43.601 --> 57:46.479
I never let any man do it
to me all the way before.

57:48.481 --> 57:50.817
None who
I agreed to, anyway.

57:50.900 --> 57:53.194
You got nothing to worry about
with me, rabbit.

57:55.864 --> 57:57.949
(PEOPLE CHATTERING EXCITEDLY)

57:58.032 --> 57:59.409
Hey. Let's go.
Get your stuff.

57:59.492 --> 58:00.577
BRUNO: Hey!

58:01.452 --> 58:02.954
- (BOTH GRUNT)
- MOLLY: Bruno!

58:03.037 --> 58:04.414
THE MAJOR: Molly! No.
Come with me.

58:04.497 --> 58:05.540
MOLLY: Leave him alone!

58:05.623 --> 58:07.041
You goddamn crumb.

58:07.125 --> 58:09.252
MOLLY: No! Let go!

58:09.335 --> 58:11.462
I warned you, didn't I?

58:11.546 --> 58:13.590
- Bruno, you're gonna kill him!
- BRUNO: Come here!

58:13.673 --> 58:15.216
(GRUNTING)

58:15.300 --> 58:16.426
MOLLY: Stop it! Let him go!

58:16.509 --> 58:18.219
- I'm gonna kill him!
- Leave him alone.

58:18.303 --> 58:20.305
Get away! I love him!
I'm leaving!

58:20.388 --> 58:23.600
Don't you understand?
I'm leaving with him!

58:23.683 --> 58:26.394
(BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY)

58:26.477 --> 58:28.521
(JAR RATTLING SOFTLY)

58:29.689 --> 58:31.232
(CAGE RATTLING)

58:33.026 --> 58:34.944
(DEEP RUMBLING)

58:35.737 --> 58:37.322
(CONTINUES RATTLING)

58:40.450 --> 58:42.368
(RATTLING CONTINUES)

58:45.955 --> 58:48.041
(PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING)

58:50.001 --> 58:51.085
(SIGHS)

58:56.466 --> 58:57.634
(SIGHS)

59:06.559 --> 59:07.894
You want the book back?

59:11.397 --> 59:12.440
No.

59:14.359 --> 59:15.360
Mm-mmm.

59:17.237 --> 59:18.696
You earned it.

59:19.822 --> 59:21.407
You worked hard for it.

59:41.302 --> 59:42.720
- (ENGINE STARTS)
- You ready?

59:42.804 --> 59:43.888
Ready for what?

59:43.972 --> 59:46.557
The world and everything
in it, rabbit. (CHUCKLES)

01:00:08.079 --> 01:00:12.542
MOLLY: One, "will."
Four, "tell."

01:00:12.625 --> 01:00:15.086
"Will you tell this lady
what she's thinking about?"

01:00:16.838 --> 01:00:18.881
Eight, "trust."

01:00:18.965 --> 01:00:20.633
"Do not trust
anyone involved."

01:00:21.676 --> 01:00:23.594
Nine, "lost."

01:00:23.678 --> 01:00:27.140
Nine, "complete,"
the loss of everything.

01:00:31.853 --> 01:00:33.980
Seven, "loneliness."

01:00:35.356 --> 01:00:39.485
Four, "tell."
Nine, "complete."

01:00:39.569 --> 01:00:42.613
"I want to tell you
about absolute loneliness."

01:00:43.948 --> 01:00:45.783
(ECHOING AND MUFFLING)
Eight, "trust."

01:00:45.867 --> 01:00:48.119
Six, "negative."

01:00:48.661 --> 01:00:50.330
(FLAME RUMBLING)

01:00:53.416 --> 01:00:54.876
(RUMBLING FADING OFF)

01:00:54.959 --> 01:00:56.627
(WHISPERING) Father.

01:00:56.711 --> 01:00:58.004
You're going now.

01:00:58.796 --> 01:01:00.048
I need you...

01:01:06.554 --> 01:01:07.680
(STAN CLEARS THROAT)

01:01:10.975 --> 01:01:12.518
Stan, are you okay?

01:01:13.853 --> 01:01:16.564
Yeah. Keep going.
We got two shows tomorrow.

01:01:19.609 --> 01:01:21.027
MOLLY: "Loneliness."

01:01:21.110 --> 01:01:23.404
Two, "fear."

01:01:23.488 --> 01:01:25.406
"Emphasis on detail."

01:01:25.490 --> 01:01:28.868
Circle.
"A prophecy fulfilled."

01:01:28.951 --> 01:01:30.286
(APPLAUSE)

01:01:32.914 --> 01:01:33.873
Wait.

01:01:36.376 --> 01:01:37.543
A woman.

01:01:38.753 --> 01:01:40.671
MOLLY: Can you
be more specific?

01:01:41.589 --> 01:01:44.008
Initials "R" or "S."

01:01:44.092 --> 01:01:45.468
(NERVOUSLY) "R."

01:01:47.261 --> 01:01:48.429
Yes.

01:01:49.514 --> 01:01:50.848
Yes, "R."

01:01:55.061 --> 01:01:57.814
I believe you know to whom
I'm speaking now, do you not?

01:01:57.897 --> 01:01:59.023
You're correct again.

01:01:59.107 --> 01:02:00.691
(APPLAUSE)

01:02:00.775 --> 01:02:02.902
(JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)

01:02:09.033 --> 01:02:10.243
STAN: You messed up.

01:02:13.788 --> 01:02:14.872
MOLLY: Stan.

01:02:27.802 --> 01:02:29.262
Stan.

01:02:29.345 --> 01:02:31.472
ANNOUNCER: <i>Next show's in 30 minutes.
Thanks, everyone.</i>

01:02:31.556 --> 01:02:33.307
All we do is rehearse it,
and you still fluff it.

01:02:33.391 --> 01:02:35.226
Out there by myself.
What happened?

01:02:35.309 --> 01:02:37.019
MOLLY: I'm sorry.
I guess I was tired.

01:02:37.103 --> 01:02:39.230
STAN: Let's see how many people
stay for the second show.

01:02:40.606 --> 01:02:42.608
(MUFFLED, INAUDIBLE
CONVERSATION)

01:02:42.692 --> 01:02:44.694
(JAZZ MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:02:47.864 --> 01:02:49.449
(CROWD APPLAUDING)

01:02:49.532 --> 01:02:50.867
STAN: A pocket watch.

01:02:51.826 --> 01:02:52.952
Gold.

01:02:53.995 --> 01:02:55.121
MOLLY: Concentrate.

01:02:55.204 --> 01:02:57.707
Do any other details
come to you?

01:02:57.790 --> 01:02:59.500
There is an inscription.

01:03:00.585 --> 01:03:01.961
Letters, am I correct?

01:03:02.503 --> 01:03:03.546
You are.

01:03:07.341 --> 01:03:08.342
Master Stanton,

01:03:08.426 --> 01:03:10.052
- can you kindly name them...
- May I?

01:03:11.304 --> 01:03:12.555
MOLLY: Yes, please
give me the object.

01:03:12.638 --> 01:03:15.016
No, thank you.
I'll hold it.

01:03:15.099 --> 01:03:17.310
Very well.

01:03:17.393 --> 01:03:21.397
Master Stanton, what is the
object being held by this lady?

01:03:25.902 --> 01:03:27.570
Well, it seems
it's a night of gold.

01:03:27.653 --> 01:03:29.405
A golden handbag.

01:03:29.489 --> 01:03:31.532
(APPLAUSE)

01:03:31.616 --> 01:03:32.909
Be quiet, child.

01:03:33.951 --> 01:03:35.953
Let me ask the questions.

01:03:37.830 --> 01:03:40.166
What is inside the bag?

01:03:43.753 --> 01:03:44.837
Madam.

01:03:45.963 --> 01:03:47.507
What is the meaning
of this?

01:03:47.590 --> 01:03:52.845
You say you're genuine and I say you use
verbal signals of some sort to communicate

01:03:52.929 --> 01:03:54.555
- between the two of you.
- (CROWD MURMURING)

01:03:58.184 --> 01:04:00.228
There are no
tricks involved, madam.

01:04:00.311 --> 01:04:02.688
There's no
deception whatsoever.

01:04:02.772 --> 01:04:04.315
Then answer me.

01:04:04.398 --> 01:04:06.609
What is inside the bag?

01:04:07.485 --> 01:04:09.779
The usual's inside that bag.

01:04:09.862 --> 01:04:12.323
Lipstick, a handkerchief.

01:04:12.406 --> 01:04:14.242
Oh, well, that is easy
enough, is it not?

01:04:14.325 --> 01:04:15.701
(PEOPLE CHUCKLE)

01:04:17.411 --> 01:04:18.871
(TUTS)

01:04:18.955 --> 01:04:22.041
Ladies and gentlemen,
I have never met this

01:04:22.667 --> 01:04:25.169
woman before.

01:04:25.253 --> 01:04:31.384
Nor have I any prior knowledge to the
contents of that purse, and yet...

01:04:31.467 --> 01:04:35.179
yet, there is something
very interesting in there.

01:04:38.432 --> 01:04:39.767
A small pistol.

01:04:39.850 --> 01:04:41.435
(CROWD GASPS)

01:04:41.519 --> 01:04:43.646
Nickel plated,
ivory handle.

01:04:45.815 --> 01:04:47.108
May I?

01:04:55.741 --> 01:04:57.243
(CROWD EXCLAIMING)

01:04:58.786 --> 01:05:00.538
(APPLAUSE)

01:05:08.671 --> 01:05:11.591
You claim to carry it to

01:05:11.674 --> 01:05:14.760
defend yourself, but...
(SMACKS LIPS)

01:05:14.844 --> 01:05:17.555
I think you do it
because you like it.

01:05:17.638 --> 01:05:22.059
I think you do it because
it makes you feel powerful.

01:05:23.936 --> 01:05:25.438
Well, madam,

01:05:26.522 --> 01:05:28.107
you are not powerful.

01:05:30.234 --> 01:05:31.652
Not powerful enough.

01:05:31.736 --> 01:05:33.404
(APPLAUSE)

01:05:39.201 --> 01:05:40.745
You are an only child,
are you not?

01:05:40.828 --> 01:05:42.997
Your mother died
when you were young?

01:05:44.790 --> 01:05:47.668
Her shadow looms large and
close, too close for comfort.

01:05:47.752 --> 01:05:48.836
Hardly a day went by

01:05:48.919 --> 01:05:52.757
in which she didn't
crush you down in small ways.

01:05:52.840 --> 01:05:58.304
And that gun,
that gun in your purse, well,

01:05:58.387 --> 01:06:01.641
sometimes you have dark thoughts
about yourself, don't you?

01:06:01.724 --> 01:06:03.100
(CROWD MURMURS)

01:06:05.603 --> 01:06:07.647
(SOFT SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

01:06:07.730 --> 01:06:09.065
(WHISPERS) Well,
don't you?

01:06:17.073 --> 01:06:18.866
Are your initials "CK"?

01:06:19.700 --> 01:06:20.826
Yes.

01:06:20.910 --> 01:06:23.162
Have you suffered a loss?
A dear one, not long ago?

01:06:23.245 --> 01:06:25.039
Oh, God. Julian?

01:06:25.122 --> 01:06:27.708
- (STAN SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)
- MAN: Go on.

01:06:27.792 --> 01:06:28.793
STAN: He's...

01:06:28.876 --> 01:06:30.252
- He's right beside you.
- (GASPS)

01:06:32.254 --> 01:06:33.881
His hand is resting
on your right shoulder.

01:06:33.964 --> 01:06:35.675
Can you feel it?

01:06:35.758 --> 01:06:38.052
Yes. He wants you
to know something.

01:06:38.135 --> 01:06:43.766
He wants you to know how
proud he is of you. And how...

01:06:43.849 --> 01:06:45.226
- (CLATTERING)
- (CROWD EXCLAIMS)

01:06:47.103 --> 01:06:48.688
(CROWD MURMURING)

01:06:50.189 --> 01:06:52.316
(APPLAUSE)

01:06:58.656 --> 01:07:00.825
(JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)

01:07:02.618 --> 01:07:04.537
(EXHALES DEEPLY, SNIFFLES)

01:07:06.414 --> 01:07:07.581
What was that about?

01:07:07.665 --> 01:07:08.958
I do not know.

01:07:09.041 --> 01:07:10.292
That was something else.

01:07:10.376 --> 01:07:11.877
See the way
that woman came after me?

01:07:11.961 --> 01:07:14.422
I saw the way you went
after her and then the man.

01:07:14.505 --> 01:07:16.549
What are you talking about?

01:07:16.632 --> 01:07:18.926
We were behind the eight.
I got us out.

01:07:19.009 --> 01:07:20.678
And why did you
keep on her, then?

01:07:20.761 --> 01:07:23.139
Well, I had to.
Crowd would've turned on us.

01:07:23.222 --> 01:07:25.850
Once she came after me,
I had to take her down.

01:07:25.933 --> 01:07:27.268
Why are you so concerned?

01:07:27.351 --> 01:07:29.311
I gave you the initials
of that watch

01:07:29.395 --> 01:07:32.022
and you turned it
into a goddamn spook show.

01:07:32.106 --> 01:07:34.567
Molly, did you see
the same show that I did?

01:07:34.650 --> 01:07:35.693
That crowd was
on its feet.

01:07:35.776 --> 01:07:37.153
When was the last time
that happened?

01:07:37.236 --> 01:07:38.779
I mean, we give them mentalism
and they treat it

01:07:38.863 --> 01:07:42.533
like it's a dog walking on its hind
legs, but that, that was different.

01:07:42.616 --> 01:07:44.785
We should leave that
in the show.

01:07:44.869 --> 01:07:47.913
Stan, that woman was sitting at the
same table as that poor, old man

01:07:47.997 --> 01:07:49.498
and I've seen
her here before.

01:07:49.582 --> 01:07:50.416
- When?
- (KNOCK ON DOOR)

01:07:51.876 --> 01:07:53.043
Hey, hepcat.

01:07:53.127 --> 01:07:55.129
You have a request.
An after show meet.

01:07:55.212 --> 01:07:56.297
Uh, thank you.

01:07:56.380 --> 01:07:58.048
- It's them.
- Oh, how do you know?

01:07:58.132 --> 01:08:00.009
Of course it's them.

01:08:00.092 --> 01:08:01.469
Then I won't see them.

01:08:01.552 --> 01:08:02.636
Oh, yes, you will.

01:08:02.720 --> 01:08:05.681
You're gonna go see that
poor, old man you spooked.

01:08:05.765 --> 01:08:08.058
Let him off the hook.
Tell him the truth.

01:08:10.311 --> 01:08:11.687
All right. Truth.

01:08:13.022 --> 01:08:14.815
And an out.

01:08:14.899 --> 01:08:16.484
And an out.
You happy?

01:08:18.402 --> 01:08:20.571
It was a good show.
You ought to give me that.

01:08:21.863 --> 01:08:23.157
Sorry to keep you waiting.

01:08:23.240 --> 01:08:25.033
Mr. Carlisle,
I don't mind waiting.

01:08:25.117 --> 01:08:26.160
I'm Charles Kimball.

01:08:26.243 --> 01:08:27.411
Judge Kimball.

01:08:27.495 --> 01:08:29.788
I was hoping to engage you
for a private consultation.

01:08:29.872 --> 01:08:31.247
STAN: Charles, may I?

01:08:38.631 --> 01:08:40.090
Uh... (SMACKS LIPS)

01:08:40.174 --> 01:08:41.175
Charles...

01:08:42.843 --> 01:08:44.053
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

01:08:45.595 --> 01:08:47.223
What you
experienced tonight...

01:08:47.305 --> 01:08:49.058
I will double
your nightly rate.

01:08:49.140 --> 01:08:50.810
Well, that's not the point.

01:08:50.893 --> 01:08:52.144
The thing is...

01:08:53.645 --> 01:08:55.022
Is she with you?

01:08:55.104 --> 01:08:57.733
Charles wanted my opinion
before engaging you.

01:08:57.817 --> 01:09:00.319
MOLLY: Well, we don't do
private consultations.

01:09:00.402 --> 01:09:01.862
Molly, please.

01:09:03.029 --> 01:09:05.658
I think Mr. Carlisle
wants an apology.

01:09:05.741 --> 01:09:07.076
STAN: Why would
I want that?

01:09:08.410 --> 01:09:10.162
You provided us with
quite a show here tonight,

01:09:10.246 --> 01:09:11.372
so thank you.

01:09:13.707 --> 01:09:14.707
(STAN SIGHS)

01:09:17.169 --> 01:09:19.505
You seek solace?

01:09:21.131 --> 01:09:22.258
CHARLES: Yes.

01:09:25.469 --> 01:09:27.388
I believe we can
provide that for you.

01:09:27.470 --> 01:09:28.721
- Stan...
- (CHARLES SIGHS IN RELIEF)

01:09:31.684 --> 01:09:33.102
I'll do it.

01:09:33.685 --> 01:09:34.562
Just this once.

01:09:34.645 --> 01:09:37.898
CHARLES: Thank you.
Mr. Carlisle, thank you.

01:09:37.982 --> 01:09:40.109
- (CHARLES SIGHS IN RELIEF)
- WOMAN: Here, Charles.

01:09:40.192 --> 01:09:41.569
Have one of mine.

01:09:45.281 --> 01:09:46.991
CHARLES:
This is my home.

01:09:47.073 --> 01:09:48.993
4:30 pm, Wednesday.

01:09:49.076 --> 01:09:50.703
I'll be there.

01:09:50.786 --> 01:09:53.288
CHARLES: Thank you,
Mr. Carlisle. Miss.

01:09:57.459 --> 01:09:59.795
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

01:10:03.257 --> 01:10:06.802
"Doctor Lilith Ritter.
Consulting psychologist."

01:10:08.137 --> 01:10:10.848
A doctor. How about that?

01:10:16.729 --> 01:10:18.856
MOLLY: Evening, Joseph.
Can I have some change, please?

01:10:18.939 --> 01:10:19.940
Yes.

01:10:20.733 --> 01:10:21.734
Thank you.

01:10:21.817 --> 01:10:22.902
STAN: I know
you're angry with me.

01:10:22.985 --> 01:10:23.944
MOLLY: Of course, you do.

01:10:24.028 --> 01:10:25.571
You can read minds.
You talk to the dead,

01:10:25.654 --> 01:10:26.739
- remember?
- Oh, come on, Molly.

01:10:26.822 --> 01:10:28.115
Why would you say yes?

01:10:28.198 --> 01:10:29.199
You saw how
desperate he was.

01:10:29.283 --> 01:10:30.409
What do you want me
to say to him?

01:10:30.492 --> 01:10:31.577
MOLLY: Say no!

01:10:31.660 --> 01:10:33.704
- STAN: Where you going?
- I have to make a phone call.

01:10:33.787 --> 01:10:35.331
Make a phone call up
in the room.

01:10:35.873 --> 01:10:36.999
Go away.

01:10:38.417 --> 01:10:41.337
I'm gonna run a bath.
You better hurry up before it gets cold.

01:10:43.088 --> 01:10:45.341
(SOFT DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

01:10:52.181 --> 01:10:53.599
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:10:54.600 --> 01:10:56.060
(BELLS JINGLING)

01:11:08.697 --> 01:11:11.200
<i>Hostilities exist.</i>

01:11:11.283 --> 01:11:13.160
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

01:11:13.243 --> 01:11:20.459
<i>There is no blinking at the fact that
our people, our territory, and our...</i>

01:11:20.542 --> 01:11:25.339
I was thinking you and I
can make a dent in this town.

01:11:25.422 --> 01:11:29.176
You and I can make a pretty
big dent in this town.

01:11:29.259 --> 01:11:32.346
I was thinking you and I can make
a pretty big dent in this town.

01:11:33.806 --> 01:11:34.932
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

01:11:45.985 --> 01:11:47.987
(MUFFLED MUSIC PLAYING)

01:11:57.329 --> 01:11:59.707
(SOFT CLASSICAL MUSIC
PLAYING ON SPEAKER)

01:12:15.222 --> 01:12:17.683
LILITH: Mr. Carlisle,
come in.

01:12:17.766 --> 01:12:19.143
STAN: Slow day?

01:12:20.769 --> 01:12:22.146
Have you not heard?

01:12:23.897 --> 01:12:25.566
We're at war.

01:12:25.649 --> 01:12:26.650
I'm aware.

01:12:28.986 --> 01:12:31.071
How did you know
it was me?

01:12:31.155 --> 01:12:32.239
What brings you here?

01:12:32.322 --> 01:12:34.116
You left me your card,
didn't you?

01:12:35.492 --> 01:12:39.580
So, here we are.

01:12:39.663 --> 01:12:41.623
Oh, not me.
I never drink.

01:12:45.294 --> 01:12:46.462
Microphones.

01:12:46.545 --> 01:12:49.089
That's right.
Wire recorder.

01:12:49.840 --> 01:12:51.175
Are you recording this?

01:12:51.258 --> 01:12:52.760
No.

01:12:52.843 --> 01:12:57.514
My office is wired to record
all analysis sessions.

01:12:57.598 --> 01:12:59.767
You got a smoother line,
but you run a racket.

01:12:59.850 --> 01:13:01.226
Same as me.

01:13:01.310 --> 01:13:02.853
Is that what this is?

01:13:03.979 --> 01:13:05.314
(KEYCHAIN CLINKING)

01:13:09.026 --> 01:13:11.195
How did you know
I had a pistol?

01:13:12.946 --> 01:13:14.615
STAN: I can read
a mark quick.

01:13:14.698 --> 01:13:15.908
Find out what they want.

01:13:18.702 --> 01:13:20.079
- (MUSIC STOPS)
- And I'm a mark, am I?

01:13:22.164 --> 01:13:24.124
What do I want?

01:13:24.208 --> 01:13:26.960
To be found out.
Same as everybody else.

01:13:28.128 --> 01:13:29.880
Is that it?

01:13:29.963 --> 01:13:33.008
Think out things that most people
want, hit 'em where they live...

01:13:33.092 --> 01:13:34.343
health, wealth, love.

01:13:34.426 --> 01:13:37.179
Find out what they're afraid
of and sell it back to them.

01:13:38.931 --> 01:13:40.682
STAN: As long as
you don't oversell it.

01:13:44.520 --> 01:13:46.522
You wanna know
how I knew about the gun?

01:13:49.233 --> 01:13:51.819
I removed the blindfold
both for dramatic effect

01:13:51.902 --> 01:13:53.904
and to get a rise
out of the audience,

01:13:53.987 --> 01:13:55.656
but also to see the way
you held your clutch.

01:13:55.739 --> 01:13:58.450
Elbow bent forward,
clutch was heavy.

01:13:58.534 --> 01:14:01.453
And you lifted it with your
left, no wedding ring.

01:14:01.537 --> 01:14:02.871
No tan mark, unmarried.

01:14:02.955 --> 01:14:04.665
So, you like to go
out at night,

01:14:04.748 --> 01:14:07.626
you were at the Copa
so you got the bees,

01:14:07.709 --> 01:14:10.379
but I assume you like to go to
lower places, too, don't you?

01:14:10.462 --> 01:14:12.589
If I want mud on my skirt,
I can find it.

01:14:12.673 --> 01:14:13.882
(CHUCKLES LIGHTLY)

01:14:13.966 --> 01:14:15.634
Well, you live alone.

01:14:15.717 --> 01:14:17.010
No man in the house.

01:14:17.094 --> 01:14:18.303
Gotta have a gun at home,

01:14:18.387 --> 01:14:20.556
but you assume yourself to be a
lady, so not a big pipe.

01:14:20.639 --> 01:14:23.684
Something small, portable, .22,
.25, four, six shot, maybe.

01:14:23.767 --> 01:14:26.895
And since you like pretty things,
nickel plated, ivory handle.

01:14:27.896 --> 01:14:30.023
But you talked
about my mother.

01:14:32.276 --> 01:14:33.944
Why?

01:14:34.027 --> 01:14:35.904
Well, dames like you
always have mommy issues.

01:14:35.988 --> 01:14:37.364
Daddy issues, too.

01:14:40.117 --> 01:14:41.910
I see.

01:14:41.994 --> 01:14:43.662
An Electra complex,
is it?

01:14:43.745 --> 01:14:44.788
I wouldn't know about that.

01:14:44.872 --> 01:14:47.708
But you're not as hard to
read as you think, lady.

01:14:47.791 --> 01:14:49.793
(SOFT SENTIMENTAL MUSIC
PLAYING)

01:14:51.962 --> 01:14:55.465
If I'm so easy to read,
why come see me then?

01:14:55.549 --> 01:14:58.385
That judge, he's a pretty
big deal in this town, is he?

01:15:01.763 --> 01:15:05.017
Judge Kimball.
Doesn't get much bigger.

01:15:05.100 --> 01:15:06.685
He a patient of yours?

01:15:07.978 --> 01:15:09.146
Friend of my father's.

01:15:09.229 --> 01:15:10.606
Y'all jazzy together?

01:15:10.689 --> 01:15:12.316
(LAUGHS DRYLY)

01:15:13.275 --> 01:15:15.402
Now, why would
you ask that?

01:15:15.485 --> 01:15:17.029
Because you have
a handle on him.

01:15:17.112 --> 01:15:18.489
His wife is
a patient of mine.

01:15:18.572 --> 01:15:20.782
- Mmm.
- Interesting woman, Felicia.

01:15:24.536 --> 01:15:26.580
Have you ever been
in analysis?

01:15:27.915 --> 01:15:29.458
I wouldn't know
what to talk about.

01:15:29.541 --> 01:15:31.293
Simple. What are you
thinking about?

01:15:31.376 --> 01:15:32.669
- Now?
- Now.

01:15:32.753 --> 01:15:33.879
You.

01:15:33.962 --> 01:15:35.005
- Me?
- Mm-hmm.

01:15:35.088 --> 01:15:36.381
- What about me?
- That you come a little closer

01:15:36.465 --> 01:15:38.008
so I can get
a better look at you.

01:15:39.343 --> 01:15:40.886
Is that why you're here?

01:15:42.054 --> 01:15:42.971
To look at me?

01:15:43.055 --> 01:15:44.640
No, I'm just thinking
that if you help me,

01:15:44.723 --> 01:15:46.934
we can make quite a
big dent in this town.

01:15:47.017 --> 01:15:48.310
- We?
- Mm-hmm.

01:15:48.393 --> 01:15:51.813
You give me something on that
judge, any of the other higher ups,

01:15:51.897 --> 01:15:54.316
I'll make it
worth your while.

01:15:54.399 --> 01:15:57.152
You think you got something big
enough or interesting enough for me?

01:15:57.236 --> 01:15:59.196
Well, nothing matters in this
goddamn world but dough,

01:15:59.279 --> 01:16:00.489
and you get that raw.

01:16:04.076 --> 01:16:05.827
All right.

01:16:05.911 --> 01:16:07.746
I'll give you something.

01:16:07.829 --> 01:16:09.164
In exchange
for the truth.

01:16:09.248 --> 01:16:10.374
Truth about what?

01:16:10.457 --> 01:16:12.000
Yourself.

01:16:12.084 --> 01:16:16.713
I give you a little information
and you tell me the truth.

01:16:25.055 --> 01:16:26.265
And don't lie.

01:16:27.849 --> 01:16:29.560
I'll know
if you're lying.

01:16:31.478 --> 01:16:32.562
That it?

01:16:35.148 --> 01:16:36.233
Shoot.

01:16:40.946 --> 01:16:42.823
Kimball lost a son.

01:16:45.242 --> 01:16:46.493
An only child.

01:16:47.911 --> 01:16:48.912
Julian.

01:16:50.122 --> 01:16:51.915
23 years old.

01:16:53.000 --> 01:16:54.459
Don't write
anything down.

01:16:56.128 --> 01:16:58.297
This is not
a carnival trick.

01:16:58.380 --> 01:17:00.340
You are to leave
no trace.

01:17:00.424 --> 01:17:02.634
No writing.
Understood.

01:17:04.886 --> 01:17:06.888
(SOFT SENTIMENTAL CONTINUES)

01:17:08.849 --> 01:17:14.271
Julian enlisted against Felicia's
wishes and died in No Man's Land.

01:17:22.029 --> 01:17:23.614
I can work with that.

01:17:23.697 --> 01:17:24.531
(APPLAUSE)

01:17:24.614 --> 01:17:27.200
Ladies and gentlemen,
thank you very much.

01:17:27.284 --> 01:17:28.410
Miss Cahill.

01:17:31.997 --> 01:17:33.332
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:17:38.670 --> 01:17:39.963
(PHONE LINE RINGING)

01:17:41.256 --> 01:17:43.383
MOLLY: I'm sorry it took
this long to call you.

01:17:43.467 --> 01:17:44.676
BRUNO: <i>Yeah. You know,</i>

01:17:44.760 --> 01:17:46.553
<i>when you didn't call
in the fall, I thought...</i>

01:17:47.971 --> 01:17:49.431
I know, I'm sorry.

01:17:50.932 --> 01:17:52.392
Do you think you all might
come to visit us

01:17:52.476 --> 01:17:54.686
before you close
for the winter?

01:17:54.770 --> 01:17:55.812
<i>Hey, Molly?</i>

01:17:57.731 --> 01:17:59.691
<i>You all right?
It's all I wanna know.</i>

01:17:59.775 --> 01:18:03.987
I'm fine. Really, I am.
Everything's Jake, Bruno.

01:18:04.071 --> 01:18:06.948
I have to go,
but I miss you all.

01:18:08.200 --> 01:18:10.744
Send my love
to The Major and to Zeena?

01:18:10.827 --> 01:18:12.704
And to everybody?

01:18:12.788 --> 01:18:13.830
<i>Anytime.</i>

01:18:13.914 --> 01:18:15.999
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

01:18:21.880 --> 01:18:23.715
So, how's this
gonna work, lady?

01:18:27.386 --> 01:18:28.678
Doctor.

01:18:30.013 --> 01:18:31.306
Doctor.

01:18:32.808 --> 01:18:34.017
Lay down, please.

01:18:39.523 --> 01:18:41.858
I think I'll just sit,
if that's okay.

01:18:41.942 --> 01:18:44.111
We can go much deeper
if you do.

01:18:45.529 --> 01:18:47.406
Why don't we just
start with sitting?

01:18:56.123 --> 01:19:00.544
When I offered you a drink,
you said you never drank.

01:19:00.627 --> 01:19:01.962
Because I don't.

01:19:03.171 --> 01:19:06.258
But you made it
a point of pride.

01:19:06.341 --> 01:19:08.343
You could've taken the glass
and not drunk.

01:19:08.427 --> 01:19:12.222
You could've said,
"Not right now," and set it aside.

01:19:12.305 --> 01:19:15.183
But you said,
"No. Not me. I never drink."

01:19:15.267 --> 01:19:16.560
You can't do
mentalism and drink.

01:19:16.643 --> 01:19:18.979
You gotta be
on your toes all the time.

01:19:19.062 --> 01:19:20.897
When you're on,
you're on.

01:19:21.565 --> 01:19:23.191
And you're on now?

01:19:23.275 --> 01:19:24.776
I'm always on, Doctor.

01:19:24.860 --> 01:19:26.778
Did your father drink?

01:19:31.241 --> 01:19:33.618
He went White Ribbon
when I was 10.

01:19:33.702 --> 01:19:35.454
But before?

01:19:35.537 --> 01:19:38.039
Clearly, before, he did,
if you knew what White Ribbon meant.

01:19:44.087 --> 01:19:47.507
When I poured the whiskey,
you winced.

01:19:48.508 --> 01:19:50.093
- Why?
- Did I?

01:19:51.136 --> 01:19:52.721
Yes.

01:19:52.804 --> 01:19:55.015
That's not something
I need to talk to you about.

01:19:55.098 --> 01:19:56.933
The truth.
We shook on it.

01:19:59.561 --> 01:20:00.896
(SIGHS)

01:20:03.565 --> 01:20:06.151
I didn't like the way
it smelled, was all.

01:20:06.234 --> 01:20:08.236
You were 12 feet away.

01:20:09.779 --> 01:20:11.948
Stuff smelled off to me.

01:20:12.032 --> 01:20:14.242
- How so?
- Smelled like wood alcohol.

01:20:15.368 --> 01:20:17.162
You drank wood alcohol?

01:20:17.245 --> 01:20:19.122
No. Not me. Never.

01:20:19.206 --> 01:20:20.457
"Never."

01:20:21.333 --> 01:20:22.709
It's that word again.

01:20:23.710 --> 01:20:25.003
Please lie down.

01:20:30.509 --> 01:20:31.676
Please.

01:20:43.104 --> 01:20:44.314
I, uh...

01:20:45.565 --> 01:20:47.943
It's a guy that I knew.

01:20:48.026 --> 01:20:51.488
He tanked up on wood alky
and he kicked off.

01:20:53.823 --> 01:20:56.660
What are you
thinking about now?

01:20:56.743 --> 01:21:00.038
(CHUCKLES) It makes no sense.

01:21:00.121 --> 01:21:01.373
Take your time.

01:21:04.668 --> 01:21:06.962
Pianos. (LAUGHING)

01:21:09.464 --> 01:21:10.632
Elaborate.

01:21:14.511 --> 01:21:15.929
(STAN BREATHES DEEPLY)

01:21:17.222 --> 01:21:18.598
My mother.

01:21:20.308 --> 01:21:22.227
Did she
play the piano?

01:21:22.310 --> 01:21:24.437
What's that have to do
with anything?

01:21:24.521 --> 01:21:25.522
Did she drink?

01:21:25.605 --> 01:21:26.940
Now and again,
like everybody else.

01:21:27.023 --> 01:21:28.608
Not you.

01:21:28.692 --> 01:21:30.068
You never drink.

01:21:31.486 --> 01:21:33.405
She was beautiful,
your mother.

01:21:36.575 --> 01:21:37.784
To me.

01:21:37.868 --> 01:21:40.078
(FAINT, MUFFLED MUSIC PLAYS)

01:21:41.204 --> 01:21:43.873
Who played the piano,
Mr. Carlisle?

01:21:43.957 --> 01:21:46.126
Guy named Humphries.

01:21:46.209 --> 01:21:50.922
He was a friend of my folks.
He was in Vaudeville.

01:21:51.006 --> 01:21:54.467
How old was the man at the carnival?
The one who died?

01:21:54.551 --> 01:21:55.594
What did you say
his name was?

01:21:55.677 --> 01:21:57.637
I didn't say.
I didn't think I said...

01:22:10.066 --> 01:22:11.192
Pete.

01:22:11.901 --> 01:22:13.028
Pete.

01:22:16.239 --> 01:22:18.491
How did Pete
get the alcohol?

01:22:18.575 --> 01:22:20.952
(LOW, UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING)

01:22:21.036 --> 01:22:22.203
I gave it to him.

01:22:22.287 --> 01:22:23.705
(FAINT RUMBLING)

01:22:25.707 --> 01:22:27.584
- (JAR RATTLES)
- But it was a mistake.

01:22:29.961 --> 01:22:31.296
Mistake?

01:22:32.964 --> 01:22:34.382
What was he to you?

01:22:34.466 --> 01:22:36.384
- Did you admire him?
- Parts of him.

01:22:36.468 --> 01:22:38.011
I think you pitied him.

01:22:39.304 --> 01:22:40.597
I don't know.

01:22:40.680 --> 01:22:43.475
He had his fair shake,
he just blew it.

01:22:43.558 --> 01:22:45.727
Did Pete teach you things?

01:22:47.437 --> 01:22:48.647
Yes.

01:22:48.730 --> 01:22:50.690
He was older,
wasn't he?

01:22:50.774 --> 01:22:52.651
He was old enough
to be your father.

01:22:53.735 --> 01:22:54.819
- (WINDOW THUDS)
- (GRUNTS)

01:22:56.446 --> 01:22:57.572
I think we've done enough.

01:22:57.656 --> 01:22:59.616
Did you ever stutter
as a child?

01:22:59.699 --> 01:23:00.867
(SNIFFS) No.

01:23:00.950 --> 01:23:03.203
Because you have a slight movement.
Compulsory movement.

01:23:03.286 --> 01:23:05.288
Your head moves up and
down, ever so slightly.

01:23:05.372 --> 01:23:07.832
- (SIGHS)
- And Humphries.

01:23:07.916 --> 01:23:10.293
Was he ever inappropriate
or abusive to you as a child?

01:23:10.377 --> 01:23:11.628
Shut your mouth.
Shut your mouth.

01:23:11.711 --> 01:23:13.713
It's all right, Stanton.
Answer me.

01:23:13.797 --> 01:23:15.048
Humphries took
my mother away

01:23:15.131 --> 01:23:17.717
because my father wasn't man enough
to hold on to her, all right?

01:23:17.801 --> 01:23:19.135
Bible spouting hypocrite.

01:23:19.219 --> 01:23:22.430
Always selling his tall tales
about Jesus and a happy afterlife.

01:23:22.514 --> 01:23:23.723
(SIGHS)

01:23:23.807 --> 01:23:24.891
(WHISPERS) And what
do you sell?

01:23:24.975 --> 01:23:26.726
I'm a hustler
and I know it.

01:23:26.810 --> 01:23:28.603
I'm on the make and I know it.
Get it?

01:23:30.021 --> 01:23:33.066
I am nothing like my old man,
and I never will be.

01:23:34.192 --> 01:23:35.443
LILITH: "Never."

01:23:36.611 --> 01:23:37.987
That word again.

01:23:40.240 --> 01:23:41.700
We're going
to work on that.

01:23:43.868 --> 01:23:45.078
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

01:23:47.706 --> 01:23:48.707
(BELL DINGS)

01:23:58.591 --> 01:24:00.802
(FAINT, MUFFLED
JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)

01:24:17.068 --> 01:24:18.903
- (LAUGHTER)
- (JAZZ MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:24:18.987 --> 01:24:20.947
BRUNO: He's working on his
disappearing act right now.

01:24:21.030 --> 01:24:22.115
ZEENA: He can't stop.

01:24:22.198 --> 01:24:23.283
- He cannot stop himself.
- BRUNO: Gonna be a headliner.

01:24:23.366 --> 01:24:24.951
Something for the road.

01:24:32.667 --> 01:24:33.960
I invited them.
Are you mad?

01:24:34.043 --> 01:24:35.128
STAN: Why would I be?

01:24:35.211 --> 01:24:37.422
(JAZZ MUSIC CONTINUES
ON SPEAKER)

01:24:39.758 --> 01:24:41.217
Hello, Stan.

01:24:41.301 --> 01:24:43.845
We're on our way to Gibtown,
thought we'd visit a while like old pals.

01:24:43.928 --> 01:24:46.347
(SMACKS LIPS, BREATHES DEEPLY)

01:24:48.433 --> 01:24:50.018
Oh, George.

01:24:51.060 --> 01:24:52.312
You guys get
something to eat?

01:24:52.395 --> 01:24:53.855
THE MAJOR: Just drinks.

01:24:53.938 --> 01:24:55.648
- Should order some food?
- Sure.

01:24:55.732 --> 01:24:57.233
How long you staying?

01:24:58.401 --> 01:24:59.986
Uh, not long.

01:25:01.237 --> 01:25:02.238
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

01:25:02.322 --> 01:25:04.324
(UPBEAT JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)

01:25:10.955 --> 01:25:12.207
Mmm.

01:25:14.375 --> 01:25:15.794
Okay. Ready?

01:25:15.877 --> 01:25:17.587
(LAUGHTER)

01:25:17.670 --> 01:25:20.006
(UPBEAT JAZZ MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:25:23.259 --> 01:25:24.803
That's right.

01:25:24.886 --> 01:25:26.596
There you go!

01:25:26.679 --> 01:25:29.098
- (MOUTHING)
- (BOTH CHUCKLE)

01:25:34.312 --> 01:25:36.481
(THE MAJOR AND MOLLY LAUGHING)

01:25:37.106 --> 01:25:39.192
You're doing well.

01:25:39.275 --> 01:25:42.403
Well, it's the same grift,
just different threads.

01:25:42.487 --> 01:25:44.155
- And...
- (BOTH LAUGH)

01:25:49.494 --> 01:25:51.412
ZEENA: (SOFTLY)
Don't do the spook show.

01:25:57.460 --> 01:25:58.962
Don't do
the spook show.

01:25:59.879 --> 01:26:01.840
Is that why
she called you?

01:26:01.923 --> 01:26:06.052
What? No. She didn't tell me.
No. It's all in the cards.

01:26:06.136 --> 01:26:08.429
Well, save it
for the chumps, Zeena.

01:26:08.513 --> 01:26:11.224
- THE MAJOR: Hah!
- (BOTH LAUGHING)

01:26:11.307 --> 01:26:13.643
Fine. Then you do it.

01:26:13.726 --> 01:26:15.937
Three card question,
it'll take two seconds.

01:26:17.730 --> 01:26:18.898
I'll oblige.

01:26:24.362 --> 01:26:25.947
Downfall.

01:26:26.030 --> 01:26:27.240
Impending danger.

01:26:32.203 --> 01:26:34.080
An urgent choice.

01:26:34.163 --> 01:26:36.416
Now, Stanton,
this is the last card.

01:26:36.499 --> 01:26:37.709
It's a decree.

01:26:37.792 --> 01:26:40.879
You turn it, you're gonna
find out what's coming to you.

01:26:47.302 --> 01:26:49.470
(SOFT OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS)

01:26:50.763 --> 01:26:52.265
The Hanged Man.

01:26:53.099 --> 01:26:54.267
It's upside down.

01:26:54.976 --> 01:26:56.060
(ZEENA GRUNTS)

01:26:57.854 --> 01:26:59.772
But you can
still choose, Stan.

01:26:59.856 --> 01:27:00.773
Well, you said
so yourself,

01:27:00.857 --> 01:27:03.026
"There's no such thing
as bad cards," remember?

01:27:04.861 --> 01:27:06.905
Just depends on what you do with it.
Look.

01:27:06.988 --> 01:27:08.990
(OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:27:09.073 --> 01:27:10.116
I fixed it.

01:27:12.535 --> 01:27:13.620
I fixed it.

01:27:19.417 --> 01:27:20.835
Keep that image
in your mind.

01:27:20.919 --> 01:27:22.128
Okay.

01:27:30.720 --> 01:27:33.222
He loved you so
very, very much.

01:27:33.306 --> 01:27:35.683
I can sense that
so clearly.

01:27:38.227 --> 01:27:40.772
Even though you didn't see
eye to eye from time to time.

01:27:40.855 --> 01:27:42.899
- Oh.
- (BOTH CHUCKLE)

01:27:42.982 --> 01:27:46.069
No, that is true.
We did not. (CHUCKLES)

01:27:47.570 --> 01:27:48.696
May I touch
that photograph?

01:27:48.780 --> 01:27:49.989
- Is that okay?
- Yes, yes.

01:27:50.073 --> 01:27:52.617
That could give me
a deeper line to him.

01:27:52.700 --> 01:27:54.869
(SNIFFLES, CLEARS THROAT)

01:28:06.089 --> 01:28:07.256
(INHALES DEEPLY)

01:28:08.216 --> 01:28:09.759
He died suddenly.

01:28:10.468 --> 01:28:11.552
(SWALLOWS)

01:28:13.012 --> 01:28:16.683
But he wants you to know
that he was in no pain.

01:28:16.766 --> 01:28:17.767
(GASPS)

01:28:19.310 --> 01:28:20.812
He wants you
to know that

01:28:21.896 --> 01:28:26.818
it hurts him
so very, very much

01:28:26.901 --> 01:28:29.237
to know that
you miss him because...

01:28:29.320 --> 01:28:30.780
well, he says
that he...

01:28:32.949 --> 01:28:35.493
He says that you should know
with absolute certainty

01:28:35.576 --> 01:28:39.539
that you will all be
together again in time.

01:28:39.622 --> 01:28:41.791
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

01:28:41.874 --> 01:28:43.418
Is he here?

01:28:43.501 --> 01:28:46.421
Is he here?
Can I speak to him?

01:28:46.504 --> 01:28:48.339
(BOTH GASPING)

01:28:49.173 --> 01:28:50.758
Speak to him. (SNIFFS)

01:28:52.385 --> 01:28:53.845
When you left...

01:28:55.471 --> 01:28:57.098
(SMACKS LIPS,
INHALES SHARPLY)

01:28:58.349 --> 01:29:02.020
you took all life
with you.

01:29:02.645 --> 01:29:03.646
(SIGHS)

01:29:04.439 --> 01:29:06.649
(SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:29:06.733 --> 01:29:10.319
Your father wanted you
to enlist, I did not.

01:29:10.403 --> 01:29:11.821
(SHUDDERS)

01:29:11.904 --> 01:29:16.034
(VOICE BREAKING) But I'm the
one who's left with nothing.

01:29:16.117 --> 01:29:17.577
(SHUDDERS)

01:29:17.660 --> 01:29:18.786
(SOFTLY) Yes.

01:29:19.787 --> 01:29:21.289
(TYPEWRITER CLACKING)

01:29:22.874 --> 01:29:24.584
Your 5:00 is here.

01:29:24.667 --> 01:29:26.502
I don't have a 5:00.

01:29:26.586 --> 01:29:27.837
(ON INTERCOM) <i>He's here.</i>

01:29:30.256 --> 01:29:31.549
Doctor.

01:29:31.632 --> 01:29:32.633
Mr. Carlisle.

01:29:34.510 --> 01:29:35.678
What's that?

01:29:35.762 --> 01:29:38.014
Your half.
That's a split. 50-50.

01:29:38.097 --> 01:29:40.475
Not interested.
I got what I wanted.

01:29:40.558 --> 01:29:42.685
But you should've
seen 'em.

01:29:42.769 --> 01:29:44.020
My God.

01:29:44.103 --> 01:29:47.065
I think they'll be talking
about that the rest of his life.

01:29:47.148 --> 01:29:50.443
And I think every time they tell it,
it'll just get better and better,

01:29:50.526 --> 01:29:51.527
bigger and bigger.

01:29:51.611 --> 01:29:53.488
A toast, then.
To your success.

01:29:53.571 --> 01:29:56.699
(SMACKS LIPS)
Uh, he asked me to, uh,

01:29:56.783 --> 01:29:58.201
see one of his friends.

01:29:59.202 --> 01:30:00.328
And who might
that be?

01:30:00.411 --> 01:30:02.080
He didn't say,
but I'm considering it.

01:30:04.290 --> 01:30:06.042
I'll tell you what,
you got a safe?

01:30:06.125 --> 01:30:08.002
(UNEASY MUSIC PLAYS)

01:30:08.086 --> 01:30:09.253
I do.

01:30:10.338 --> 01:30:11.255
Why don't you
keep this for me?

01:30:11.339 --> 01:30:14.050
I don't want Molly to know
about it anyway.

01:30:14.133 --> 01:30:16.010
Why don't you keep it
for a few days?

01:30:16.094 --> 01:30:19.305
If you change your mind,
we'll spilt it 50-50.

01:30:19.388 --> 01:30:21.057
And if not,
I'll keep it.

01:30:30.233 --> 01:30:31.692
You barely know me.

01:30:33.653 --> 01:30:34.946
(SMACKS LIPS)

01:30:35.029 --> 01:30:36.447
Oh, I know you well.

01:30:36.531 --> 01:30:38.825
(UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:30:40.535 --> 01:30:41.786
I know...

01:30:43.496 --> 01:30:44.956
you're no good.

01:30:48.960 --> 01:30:50.461
And I know that 'cause...

01:30:53.214 --> 01:30:54.674
neither am I.

01:30:57.260 --> 01:30:58.761
Is that so?

01:31:01.556 --> 01:31:02.640
Yes.

01:31:05.184 --> 01:31:07.436
(MUFFLED JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)

01:31:10.690 --> 01:31:12.275
MOLLY: You're asking
for the shape.

01:31:15.945 --> 01:31:17.572
What if I do two?

01:31:20.491 --> 01:31:21.659
Color.

01:31:24.954 --> 01:31:26.205
That's good.

01:31:32.795 --> 01:31:34.463
I'm too hard on us.

01:31:36.257 --> 01:31:38.551
No, you're right about it.

01:31:38.634 --> 01:31:39.927
You need a break.

01:31:43.848 --> 01:31:45.641
Whatever you wanna do,
we'll do.

01:31:48.227 --> 01:31:49.520
Can we go dancing?

01:31:49.604 --> 01:31:50.688
Absolutely.

01:31:50.771 --> 01:31:51.939
ANNOUNCER: (ON PA)
<i>Call for Stanton Carlisle.</i>

01:31:52.023 --> 01:31:53.191
(IMITATES ANNOUNCER MOCKINGLY)

01:31:53.274 --> 01:31:54.484
Whatever you want.

01:31:54.567 --> 01:31:55.234
ANNOUNCER: <i>You can
pick it up on house phone.</i>

01:31:55.318 --> 01:31:57.778
We'll go tonight
after the show.

01:31:57.862 --> 01:31:59.989
I'm dying in here, Stan.

01:32:03.242 --> 01:32:04.493
I love you.

01:32:17.381 --> 01:32:18.966
Yeah.

01:32:19.050 --> 01:32:23.095
LILITH: <i>The man Kimball wants to
introduce you to is Ezra Grindle.</i>

01:32:23.179 --> 01:32:26.265
Grindle was a patient of mine
for a brief time.

01:32:26.349 --> 01:32:28.059
He's unstable.
Unpredictable.

01:32:30.770 --> 01:32:31.771
How is he fixed for dough?

01:32:31.854 --> 01:32:34.315
<i>Oh, he's very rich.
Very powerful.</i>

01:32:34.398 --> 01:32:36.817
<i>And intensely private.</i>

01:32:36.901 --> 01:32:39.528
Dealings with Grindle
have consequences.

01:32:39.612 --> 01:32:40.738
Permanent ones.

01:32:43.616 --> 01:32:45.409
Well, you better
give me an angle.

01:32:45.493 --> 01:32:47.703
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

01:33:05.137 --> 01:33:08.975
Coat, hat, and gloves
on the counter.

01:33:09.058 --> 01:33:11.102
And empty your pockets.

01:33:11.185 --> 01:33:16.023
No pencils, no pens, no keys,
no cigarettes, or lighter.

01:33:19.735 --> 01:33:20.820
Hands up.

01:33:24.573 --> 01:33:25.658
Turn around.

01:33:26.993 --> 01:33:28.995
I need your watch
and your ring.

01:33:31.372 --> 01:33:32.790
Manners, friend.

01:33:33.874 --> 01:33:34.917
What was that?

01:33:35.001 --> 01:33:36.502
You should say "please."

01:33:38.587 --> 01:33:39.588
Please.

01:33:52.810 --> 01:33:54.145
Mr. Carlisle.

01:33:55.187 --> 01:33:56.564
I'm Ezra Grindle.

01:33:57.023 --> 01:33:58.065
(DOOR SHUTS)

01:33:59.400 --> 01:34:01.277
Let me take your jacket.

01:34:01.360 --> 01:34:02.361
Please.

01:34:04.363 --> 01:34:06.115
I'm very wary
of appearing in public,

01:34:06.198 --> 01:34:08.618
so I want to thank you
for coming to see me.

01:34:08.701 --> 01:34:10.077
A man of your talents.

01:34:10.161 --> 01:34:11.954
Well, that's very
kind of you.

01:34:12.038 --> 01:34:13.873
Wouldn't count on that.
(CHUCKLES)

01:34:14.749 --> 01:34:15.875
Take a seat.

01:34:20.463 --> 01:34:22.131
What is this?

01:34:22.214 --> 01:34:24.550
This is our version
of a polygraph.

01:34:25.509 --> 01:34:26.635
You familiar with the term?

01:34:26.719 --> 01:34:28.554
You call it a lie detector.

01:34:29.764 --> 01:34:31.557
You'd like to
perform this on me?

01:34:31.640 --> 01:34:32.892
That's the general idea, yeah.

01:34:32.975 --> 01:34:34.185
(LAUGHS)

01:34:35.478 --> 01:34:36.937
MAN: We will measure
your blood pressure,

01:34:37.021 --> 01:34:40.775
respiration, involuntary
muscle contractions.

01:34:40.858 --> 01:34:42.777
Not sure how comfortable
I am with this.

01:34:42.860 --> 01:34:45.988
Well, we've had our share of
snake charmers in the past.

01:34:46.072 --> 01:34:47.615
We deal with them.

01:34:47.698 --> 01:34:48.991
Raise your arms, please.

01:34:51.243 --> 01:34:53.204
I don't think
this is necessary.

01:34:53.287 --> 01:34:54.955
Can you watch
my tie, please?

01:34:55.915 --> 01:34:57.708
- I'll watch it.
- Thank you.

01:34:57.792 --> 01:34:59.794
And what happens
if I fail?

01:34:59.877 --> 01:35:03.422
One thing at a time, hmm?

01:35:03.506 --> 01:35:06.967
MAN: I will ask you simple
questions to establish our baseline.

01:35:07.051 --> 01:35:08.677
You will answer
in short sentences,

01:35:08.761 --> 01:35:11.138
only what you believe
to be absolute truth.

01:35:12.848 --> 01:35:15.267
- (POLYGRAPH POWERS UP)
- "Absolute truth."

01:35:15.351 --> 01:35:17.353
(SNIFFS) I can do that.

01:35:20.940 --> 01:35:22.066
Now,

01:35:22.149 --> 01:35:25.027
brief as you can,
what is your name?

01:35:25.111 --> 01:35:26.487
STAN: Stanton Carlisle.

01:35:27.738 --> 01:35:29.407
MAN: What year are we in?

01:35:30.366 --> 01:35:33.202
(SNIFFS) 1941.

01:35:33.285 --> 01:35:34.370
MAN: Good.

01:35:34.453 --> 01:35:36.247
What day is today?

01:35:36.330 --> 01:35:37.331
(STAN LAUGHS)

01:35:38.749 --> 01:35:40.209
Wednesday, I think.

01:35:42.002 --> 01:35:43.879
Who is the president
of the United States?

01:35:44.422 --> 01:35:45.548
Roosevelt.

01:35:48.259 --> 01:35:53.514
Very well. Now, as briefly as you
can, are you a true medium?

01:35:53.597 --> 01:35:54.598
Yes, I am.

01:35:59.854 --> 01:36:00.855
Can you read minds?

01:36:00.938 --> 01:36:04.358
Yes, I can.
Under the right circumstances.

01:36:06.610 --> 01:36:07.611
Brief.

01:36:09.238 --> 01:36:11.449
Keep your answers
brief, please.

01:36:11.532 --> 01:36:14.034
Now, are you in contact
with the beyond?

01:36:27.423 --> 01:36:29.300
Before we go on,
there's a...

01:36:33.429 --> 01:36:36.056
There is a presence
in this room.

01:36:36.140 --> 01:36:37.349
Right now.

01:36:39.560 --> 01:36:41.479
It's a female presence.

01:36:45.649 --> 01:36:47.651
(SOFT SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

01:36:50.905 --> 01:36:54.033
She's just insisting,
she's insisting that this...

01:36:56.202 --> 01:36:57.828
that she communicate
with somebody.

01:36:57.912 --> 01:37:00.289
Is it me? Do you wanna
communicate with me?

01:37:00.372 --> 01:37:01.665
Is it him?

01:37:03.292 --> 01:37:04.627
Oh, it's you, Mr. Grindle.

01:37:08.214 --> 01:37:09.465
I don't... I don't...

01:37:12.635 --> 01:37:15.846
Oh. She... She passed away
many years ago.

01:37:18.390 --> 01:37:19.683
Oh, but there was...

01:37:22.228 --> 01:37:24.313
Yeah, there was
a life extinguished with it.

01:37:24.396 --> 01:37:25.648
And it... it...

01:37:29.151 --> 01:37:31.237
Oh, it was a child.
It was a baby.

01:37:35.324 --> 01:37:37.493
You forced her to miscarry,
did you not?

01:37:39.912 --> 01:37:41.956
(SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:37:49.547 --> 01:37:50.548
Shall I go on?

01:37:50.965 --> 01:37:51.966
No.

01:37:52.841 --> 01:37:54.426
There's no need.

01:37:55.594 --> 01:37:57.513
A word in my office,
gentlemen.

01:38:00.850 --> 01:38:02.059
You said you were
gonna fine-tune it.

01:38:02.142 --> 01:38:03.060
MAN: Yes, sir.

01:38:03.143 --> 01:38:04.728
GRINDLE:
You fine-tuned it incorrectly?

01:38:04.812 --> 01:38:05.771
- MAN: No, no, no.
- CHARLES: Ezra...

01:38:05.854 --> 01:38:07.106
- GRINDLE: You had two and two.
- (DOOR CLOSES)

01:38:07.189 --> 01:38:08.190
Two wrong, two right.

01:38:08.274 --> 01:38:10.109
- (MUFFLED CONVERSATION)
- (STAN SIGHS)

01:38:10.192 --> 01:38:11.402
Stop, stop!

01:38:11.485 --> 01:38:13.654
Answer me this, you brought
him straight from the club.

01:38:13.737 --> 01:38:15.364
How could he know that? How?

01:38:15.447 --> 01:38:17.825
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

01:38:45.060 --> 01:38:46.061
Well,

01:38:47.146 --> 01:38:48.689
got him hooked real good.

01:38:50.566 --> 01:38:51.775
Despite all that.

01:38:57.615 --> 01:38:59.241
He's got quite
an operation.

01:39:00.284 --> 01:39:01.827
And he's gonna
call back?

01:39:04.830 --> 01:39:06.624
Oh, yeah,
he's gonna call back.

01:39:06.707 --> 01:39:08.417
I left real money
on the table.

01:39:09.501 --> 01:39:11.378
Gotta leave money
to get money.

01:39:20.220 --> 01:39:22.556
You're gonna have to give me
some real information on him now.

01:39:22.640 --> 01:39:24.266
No. Not me.

01:39:27.394 --> 01:39:28.646
(STAN SMACKS LIPS)

01:39:29.396 --> 01:39:30.731
I figured.

01:39:32.941 --> 01:39:35.486
I'm the only one who could've
given you that information.

01:39:37.821 --> 01:39:39.782
If your foot slips,

01:39:40.991 --> 01:39:42.034
we both fall.

01:39:49.833 --> 01:39:51.752
Don't worry.
I'll figure it out.

01:39:55.047 --> 01:39:56.298
I mean, this guy's, uh,

01:39:57.758 --> 01:40:00.052
he's real deep
on the spook dodge.

01:40:01.261 --> 01:40:02.554
(KEYCHAIN CLINKS SOFTLY)

01:40:05.683 --> 01:40:07.142
I don't think
you have a problem.

01:40:08.477 --> 01:40:09.978
I'd say he's very desperate.

01:40:13.023 --> 01:40:14.900
Don't worry. They'll never
trace it back to you.

01:40:16.068 --> 01:40:17.820
(KEYCHAIN CLINKING SOFTLY)

01:40:27.079 --> 01:40:28.997
The thing
you need to know is,

01:40:30.249 --> 01:40:33.502
if you displease
the right people,

01:40:33.585 --> 01:40:37.297
the world closes in on you
very, very fast.

01:40:39.508 --> 01:40:41.719
(SOFT SENTIMENTAL MUSIC
PLAYING)

01:41:01.780 --> 01:41:03.365
What happened to you?

01:41:06.702 --> 01:41:07.786
Life.

01:41:11.415 --> 01:41:12.916
Life happened to me.

01:41:20.966 --> 01:41:22.551
(KISSING)

01:41:30.309 --> 01:41:32.478
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

01:41:51.580 --> 01:41:53.248
LILITH: (ON RECORDING)
<i>Patient Ezra Grindle.</i>

01:41:53.332 --> 01:41:55.167
<i>Therapy session number four.</i>

01:41:55.250 --> 01:41:57.377
GRINDLE: <i>I am alone.</i>

01:41:57.461 --> 01:41:59.046
<i>Lost.</i>

01:41:59.129 --> 01:42:01.173
<i>I feel lost.</i>

01:42:01.256 --> 01:42:03.258
<i>Everything I earn
feels hollow.</i>

01:42:03.342 --> 01:42:05.385
LILITH:
<i>Would you elaborate, please?</i>

01:42:07.179 --> 01:42:09.473
GRINDLE: <i>May, 1901.</i>

01:42:09.556 --> 01:42:11.558
<i>The last time I saw her alive.</i>

01:42:12.726 --> 01:42:15.145
<i>I didn't... I...</i>

01:42:15.229 --> 01:42:16.480
"Doris Mae Cable."

01:42:16.563 --> 01:42:17.898
GRINDLE: <i>I couldn't
claim her body.</i>

01:42:17.981 --> 01:42:19.858
...property for
register number 28030.

01:42:19.942 --> 01:42:21.735
GRINDLE: <i>Because
I would've been ruined.</i>

01:42:23.487 --> 01:42:26.824
<i>So my love went
to a commoners' grave.</i>

01:42:26.907 --> 01:42:28.325
Thank you kindly.

01:42:34.998 --> 01:42:37.084
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:42:47.970 --> 01:42:49.263
There you are.

01:43:11.201 --> 01:43:12.452
(SIGHS)

01:43:25.591 --> 01:43:27.593
(WIND WHISTLING)

01:43:52.409 --> 01:43:53.702
(GRINDLE GRUNTS)

01:43:54.578 --> 01:43:55.913
(WHISPERS INDISTINCTLY)

01:43:55.996 --> 01:43:58.624
GRINDLE: So I wanted to know
what impression you got from her.

01:43:58.707 --> 01:44:01.960
The girl that, uh,
you sensed during the test.

01:44:02.044 --> 01:44:03.378
I didn't see her.

01:44:03.462 --> 01:44:04.880
She didn't materialize.

01:44:06.214 --> 01:44:09.134
GRINDLE: But by that,
you mean she could?

01:44:09.217 --> 01:44:11.720
STAN: Well, it was very brief,
uh, Mr. Grindle.

01:44:11.803 --> 01:44:13.639
GRINDLE: Uh, Ezra, please.

01:44:13.722 --> 01:44:17.851
STAN: I sensed
profound sadness and regret.

01:44:18.852 --> 01:44:20.687
She loved you.

01:44:20.771 --> 01:44:23.857
And that boy.
That baby boy.

01:44:29.237 --> 01:44:30.781
It was a boy?

01:44:33.200 --> 01:44:34.534
Is she with me?

01:44:35.369 --> 01:44:36.787
She's never far.

01:44:40.040 --> 01:44:43.085
This place important to you?
This garden?

01:44:43.168 --> 01:44:46.713
Yes. I built it,
uh, to honor her.

01:44:46.797 --> 01:44:50.050
The paths and the benches,
you see?

01:44:50.133 --> 01:44:51.510
She would've loved it.

01:44:51.593 --> 01:44:52.928
She does.

01:44:53.762 --> 01:44:54.930
I can sense it.

01:44:58.809 --> 01:45:00.477
Brother Ezra, she...

01:45:00.560 --> 01:45:02.396
she's trying to
tell me something.

01:45:02.479 --> 01:45:04.690
It doesn't make
any sense.

01:45:04.773 --> 01:45:07.609
Sometimes they communicate
like that. It gets jumbled.

01:45:08.694 --> 01:45:10.153
The letter "D."

01:45:14.032 --> 01:45:16.368
Dorrie? Dorrie, is it?

01:45:19.496 --> 01:45:20.455
(SHUDDERS)

01:45:24.543 --> 01:45:26.461
(GRINDLE PANTING)

01:45:28.630 --> 01:45:30.507
I wanna see...
(VOICE BREAKS)

01:45:30.590 --> 01:45:32.259
Oh, I have to
see her again.

01:45:32.342 --> 01:45:33.552
Whatever it takes.

01:45:33.635 --> 01:45:36.221
I want you to...
(SNIFFLES) Uh...

01:45:36.930 --> 01:45:38.306
- Materialize her?
- Yeah.

01:45:39.599 --> 01:45:41.435
Do you have any idea
what would be required

01:45:41.518 --> 01:45:43.103
for something
like that to occur?

01:45:43.186 --> 01:45:47.315
(GRUNTS) I'll commit $10,000
for every session we have.

01:45:52.112 --> 01:45:53.697
Mr. Grindle.

01:45:55.073 --> 01:45:56.700
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

01:45:56.783 --> 01:45:58.493
Your sins are grave.

01:46:01.079 --> 01:46:02.914
You would have to
work hard,

01:46:03.749 --> 01:46:05.584
spiritually,

